txt-'1.1.1.6',
text_type-5,
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'HUNDERTWASSER&rsquo;S LETTER 
IN ANSWER TO REQUESTS FOR 
A GIFT OF AN ORIGINAL WORK

',
text_title_ge-'HUNDERTWASSERS ANTWORTBRIEF AN LEUTE, DIE IHN UM DAS GESCHENK EINES ORIGINALWERKES BITTEN',
text_keywords-'request, gift, postcard, reproduction, value, certificate, graphic work, Bittbrief, Geschenk, Postkarte, Reprodution, Wert, Zertifikat, Graphik',
text_date-'1995-02-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Our true illiteracy is our inability to be creative&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Paris&lt;/em&gt;, 1956&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Dear friend,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Thank you for your letter. I have received so many letters with the same request by this time that I have written down a standard reply. I don&rsquo;t have that here, so I&rsquo;ll answer again.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I hope you have no objections if I use this letter as a standard reply to other requests of this kind, such as, &ldquo;How can I, with my normal income, acquire a Hundertwasser original?&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;A number of widely divergent aspects are involved here.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The most direct answer is that &ldquo;people with normal incomes&rdquo; buy automobiles and drive them around, although it would be more environmentally friendly and cheaper to use bicycles, trains and busses. Millions of cars are bought by people with normal incomes on an instalment plan or with a loan. The prices are similar &ndash; but the car&rsquo;s condition deteriorates. A painting makes it possible to take a longer trip to a more beautiful world.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;A different aspect: does one want a painting for its intrinsic or its financial value? I am myself a collector of art works and am very happy to have them. I take my collection along with me whenever I travel. I have all my favourites with me: Bonnard, Rousseau, Schiele, Klimt, Paolo Uccello, &ldquo;Les tr&egrave;s riches heures du Duc de Berry&rdquo;, B&ouml;cklin (&ldquo;The Isle of the Dead&rdquo;), Van Gogh, Kumpf, Gauguin, Dix, Breughel, Caspar David Friedrich, Indian miniatures and many, many more.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Some of the postcards in my collection are very worn from being looked at so much. Some are hard to get. Wherever I am, in Paris, Venice, Vienna, America, my first stop is a good bookshop, to add to my collection. In Oslo, for instance, I discovered painters I had never heard of, on postcards! J. C. Dahl and Harald Sohlberg, for example. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I am sending you, dear friend, a few postcards from my collection which I like very much and have duplicates of. I can&rsquo;t part with my favourites. But perhaps this can be the beginning of your collection. The terrific thing about it is that one can dream wherever one holds them in one&rsquo;s hand: in the tram, the waiting room, on holiday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;A third aspect: it was always my goal to have as many people derive pleasure from my art as possible. But to keep everyone happy I would have to produce paintings on a conveyor belt which keeps getting faster and faster, like a machine gun. About 1000 paintings a day is humanly impossible, even if I paint extremely fast. (Now it is about four to six paintings a year, because I am increasingly busy with architecture.)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;This means that my paintings can only get cheaper if they are not as good, or I would have to &ldquo;produce&rdquo; so many that I can no longer imbue them with a heart and soul.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;It is not possible for thousands of people to have children by one woman, if this woman can only have a child every nine months, and certainly no more than twenty times.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Painting pictures is a creative act, and a difficult one at that, because it requires utmost concentration, dedication, honesty, original creativity, unrepeatability; it is done with the heart and in harmony with creation, with nature &ndash; and all these things not intellectually, but &ldquo;unconsciously&rdquo;, with feeling. All this needs time to come about, just as a tree needs time to grow.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;It is almost as if I had to apologize for the value of my paintings. But monetary value comes about in the free market through supply and demand, and I can&rsquo;t influence that. Even if I give my paintings away, they have the same value as the prices on the international art market and at auctions. It is just like the water level in connected receptacles.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;That is why I ceased selling my paintings thirty years ago and instead see to it that they are exhibited in museums and galleries, where they can be seen by many people. Just working for the elite, who have the paintings &ldquo;for themselves&rdquo; or even store them in bank vaults, is repugnant to me.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;By the way: expensive works of art require expensive installations, security against burglary, alarm systems, surveillance services and air-conditioning, humidifiers and warning systems for acidity, heat, aridity, which means that the owner of a work of art has a responsibility like that for a child.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Moreover, every work has an &oelig;uvre number and a file, with a transparency of it, its origin, curriculum vitae and documentation and a kind of identity folder, called its &ldquo;certificat d&rsquo;authenticit&eacute;&rdquo;, in several languages. The contents of the certificate: photograph, photographs of various work stages, technique, dimensions, where it was done, list of exhibitions, list of reproductions, list of collectors (paintings often change hands over twenty times), remarks on the signature, damage, source of materials, pointers on preservation and loan obligation for exhibitions and mandatory provision of information regarding changes in ownership.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;This is why in the past twenty-five years I have decided instead to refine and perfect graphics and reproductions more and more, to the point that they far surpass the original paintings in expressiveness, intensity and, in part, durability.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Signed original graphics are mixed-media works in their own right which cannot be copied and where techniques come into play which cannot be achieved in painting, e.g., metal embossing in many colours, fluorescent paints and others which glow in the dark, colour depth through glazing techniques and glass-bead effects. Because I was so intent on outdoing the originals in the reproductions, which amounted to the continuation of the paint-ing, perfecting it, the price of the graphics increased, too, and that of the reproductions, if only because of the complicated printing technology involved, with many more colours than customary.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Another aspect: it is ill will, or not pure, but financial interest when people say my paintings are too expensive. There are works affordable for anyone: from postage stamps for 1 DM, which are true masterworks of engraving (to be looked at with the magnifying glass), to postcards, reproductions in books and calendars, to posters and large, high-quality reproductions, original graphics, tapestries of paintings in mixed media, works are available in every price category.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Another aspect: I have often answered letters like yours by giving the writer a painting. Only the letters were more aggressive, something like this: &ldquo;I am a poor student; I love your pictures, but can&rsquo;t afford them. You paint for the capitalist pigs. If you don&rsquo;t want to be a pig yourself, give me a picture.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;So I did, several times. When I visited the man three weeks later, the painting had been sold. He gave in explanation, as he couldn&rsquo;t afford to acquire a painting of mine, he couldn&rsquo;t afford to keep it either. Almost all the gifts of this kind ended this way, I think it&rsquo;s even 100 %! The painting had to be sold because his mother or his wife had cancer and they needed the money for the operation. Your painting or your life. Life has priority. Or divorce. They couldn&rsquo;t agree on whom the painting belonged to. Or they had to raise a large sum of money at once or the mortgage on the house would have been foreclosed and they would have ended up on the street.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Or they had to post bail to get someone out of jail. Or raise a large sum of money immediately, tax-free, for a house or real-estate deal. Tomorrow would have been too late, etc., etc.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;All this and much more I have already experienced.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;None of the paintings I gave away remained unsold with the recipient. Usually already within three weeks, or even by the next day!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Another aspect: one should buy paintings which one loves as long as they are not expensive. The great, famous collections, by Vollard, Kahnweiler, Guggenheim and others, with Picassos, Van Goghs, etc., which now cost hundreds of millions, were for the most part put together at an early stage for a pittance per picture.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I remember very well giving away paintings myself in 1950&ndash;1960 for a pittance or a dinner or a cup of coffee, out of sheer joy that someone was interested in my work. Picasso had only one pair of trousers; when he had them taken to the cleaners, he had to stay in bed, and a collector retrieved his trousers for him.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;There are now many unknown painters who are better than Van Gogh or I, only they work in obscurity. But they can be found at art exhibitions, sometimes even at auctions and in the circles of their friends, and they can be bought very cheaply, just like Van Gogh and Gauguin in their time, and they will be the great names of the future.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Also, pictures by children, framed, for example, can be head and shoulders above any Van Gogh. You just have to look around a bit. Even in newspapers you can often find masterpieces!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The greatest satisfaction is to be actively creative oneself and not to consume art passively. To get to know one&rsquo;s self, one&rsquo;s own roots. When one sees the world through the eyes of others, one is not free. The journey to oneself makes one infinitely happy, and it is the only journey possible in order to gain justification for leading the existence of an independent, individual, creative being in this world. Otherwise one is and remains a slave, a toy of the short-lived interests of others.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Much more could be said.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Our true illiteracy is our inability to be creative&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Paris&lt;/em&gt;, 1956&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Dear friend,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Thank you for your letter. I have received so many letters with the same request by this time that I have written down a standard reply. I don&rsquo;t have that here, so I&rsquo;ll answer again.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I hope you have no objections if I use this letter as a standard reply to other requests of this kind, such as, &ldquo;How can I, with my normal income, acquire a Hundertwasser original?&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;A number of widely divergent aspects are involved here.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The most direct answer is that &ldquo;people with normal incomes&rdquo; buy automobiles and drive them around, although it would be more environmentally friendly and cheaper to use bicycles, trains and busses. Millions of cars are bought by people with normal incomes on an instalment plan or with a loan. The prices are similar &ndash; but the car&rsquo;s condition deteriorates. A painting makes it possible to take a longer trip to a more beautiful world.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;A different aspect: does one want a painting for its intrinsic or its financial value? I am myself a collector of art works and am very happy to have them. I take my collection along with me whenever I travel. I have all my favourites with me: Bonnard, Rousseau, Schiele, Klimt, Paolo Uccello, &ldquo;Les tr&egrave;s riches heures du Duc de Berry&rdquo;, B&ouml;cklin (&ldquo;The Isle of the Dead&rdquo;), Van Gogh, Kumpf, Gauguin, Dix, Breughel, Caspar David Friedrich, Indian miniatures and many, many more.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Some of the postcards in my collection are very worn from being looked at so much. Some are hard to get. Wherever I am, in Paris, Venice, Vienna, America, my first stop is a good bookshop, to add to my collection. In Oslo, for instance, I discovered painters I had never heard of, on postcards! J. C. Dahl and Harald Sohlberg, for example. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I am sending you, dear friend, a few postcards from my collection which I like very much and have duplicates of. I can&rsquo;t part with my favourites. But perhaps this can be the beginning of your collection. The terrific thing about it is that one can dream wherever one holds them in one&rsquo;s hand: in the tram, the waiting room, on holiday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;A third aspect: it was always my goal to have as many people derive pleasure from my art as possible. But to keep everyone happy I would have to produce paintings on a conveyor belt which keeps getting faster and faster, like a machine gun. About 1000 paintings a day is humanly impossible, even if I paint extremely fast. (Now it is about four to six paintings a year, because I am increasingly busy with architecture.)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;This means that my paintings can only get cheaper if they are not as good, or I would have to &ldquo;produce&rdquo; so many that I can no longer imbue them with a heart and soul.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;It is not possible for thousands of people to have children by one woman, if this woman can only have a child every nine months, and certainly no more than twenty times.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Painting pictures is a creative act, and a difficult one at that, because it requires utmost concentration, dedication, honesty, original creativity, unrepeatability; it is done with the heart and in harmony with creation, with nature &ndash; and all these things not intellectually, but &ldquo;unconsciously&rdquo;, with feeling. All this needs time to come about, just as a tree needs time to grow.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;It is almost as if I had to apologize for the value of my paintings. But monetary value comes about in the free market through supply and demand, and I can&rsquo;t influence that. Even if I give my paintings away, they have the same value as the prices on the international art market and at auctions. It is just like the water level in connected receptacles.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;That is why I ceased selling my paintings thirty years ago and instead see to it that they are exhibited in museums and galleries, where they can be seen by many people. Just working for the elite, who have the paintings &ldquo;for themselves&rdquo; or even store them in bank vaults, is repugnant to me.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;By the way: expensive works of art require expensive installations, security against burglary, alarm systems, surveillance services and air-conditioning, humidifiers and warning systems for acidity, heat, aridity, which means that the owner of a work of art has a responsibility like that for a child.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Moreover, every work has an &oelig;uvre number and a file, with a transparency of it, its origin, curriculum vitae and documentation and a kind of identity folder, called its &ldquo;certificat d&rsquo;authenticit&eacute;&rdquo;, in several languages. The contents of the certificate: photograph, photographs of various work stages, technique, dimensions, where it was done, list of exhibitions, list of reproductions, list of collectors (paintings often change hands over twenty times), remarks on the signature, damage, source of materials, pointers on preservation and loan obligation for exhibitions and mandatory provision of information regarding changes in ownership.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;This is why in the past twenty-five years I have decided instead to refine and perfect graphics and reproductions more and more, to the point that they far surpass the original paintings in expressiveness, intensity and, in part, durability.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Signed original graphics are mixed-media works in their own right which cannot be copied and where techniques come into play which cannot be achieved in painting, e.g., metal embossing in many colours, fluorescent paints and others which glow in the dark, colour depth through glazing techniques and glass-bead effects. Because I was so intent on outdoing the originals in the reproductions, which amounted to the continuation of the paint-ing, perfecting it, the price of the graphics increased, too, and that of the reproductions, if only because of the complicated printing technology involved, with many more colours than customary.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Another aspect: it is ill will, or not pure, but financial interest when people say my paintings are too expensive. There are works affordable for anyone: from postage stamps for 1 DM, which are true masterworks of engraving (to be looked at with the magnifying glass), to postcards, reproductions in books and calendars, to posters and large, high-quality reproductions, original graphics, tapestries of paintings in mixed media, works are available in every price category.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Another aspect: I have often answered letters like yours by giving the writer a painting. Only the letters were more aggressive, something like this: &ldquo;I am a poor student; I love your pictures, but can&rsquo;t afford them. You paint for the capitalist pigs. If you don&rsquo;t want to be a pig yourself, give me a picture.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;So I did, several times. When I visited the man three weeks later, the painting had been sold. He gave in explanation, as he couldn&rsquo;t afford to acquire a painting of mine, he couldn&rsquo;t afford to keep it either. Almost all the gifts of this kind ended this way, I think it&rsquo;s even 100 %! The painting had to be sold because his mother or his wife had cancer and they needed the money for the operation. Your painting or your life. Life has priority. Or divorce. They couldn&rsquo;t agree on whom the painting belonged to. Or they had to raise a large sum of money at once or the mortgage on the house would have been foreclosed and they would have ended up on the street.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Or they had to post bail to get someone out of jail. Or raise a large sum of money immediately, tax-free, for a house or real-estate deal. Tomorrow would have been too late, etc., etc.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;All this and much more I have already experienced.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;None of the paintings I gave away remained unsold with the recipient. Usually already within three weeks, or even by the next day!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Another aspect: one should buy paintings which one loves as long as they are not expensive. The great, famous collections, by Vollard, Kahnweiler, Guggenheim and others, with Picassos, Van Goghs, etc., which now cost hundreds of millions, were for the most part put together at an early stage for a pittance per picture.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I remember very well giving away paintings myself in 1950&ndash;1960 for a pittance or a dinner or a cup of coffee, out of sheer joy that someone was interested in my work. Picasso had only one pair of trousers; when he had them taken to the cleaners, he had to stay in bed, and a collector retrieved his trousers for him.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;There are now many unknown painters who are better than Van Gogh or I, only they work in obscurity. But they can be found at art exhibitions, sometimes even at auctions and in the circles of their friends, and they can be bought very cheaply, just like Van Gogh and Gauguin in their time, and they will be the great names of the future.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Also, pictures by children, framed, for example, can be head and shoulders above any Van Gogh. You just have to look around a bit. Even in newspapers you can often find masterpieces!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The greatest satisfaction is to be actively creative oneself and not to consume art passively. To get to know one&rsquo;s self, one&rsquo;s own roots. When one sees the world through the eyes of others, one is not free. The journey to oneself makes one infinitely happy, and it is the only journey possible in order to gain justification for leading the existence of an independent, individual, creative being in this world. Otherwise one is and remains a slave, a toy of the short-lived interests of others.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Much more could be said.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Unser wahres Analphabetentum ist das Unverm&ouml;gen, kreativ sch&ouml;pferisch t&auml;tig zu sein.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Paris 1956&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Lieber Freund,&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;danke f&uuml;r Ihren Brief. Ich habe schon so viele Brie&shy;fe mit der gleichen Frage erhalten, da&szlig; ich einen Antwortbrief aufge&shy;setzt habe. Den habe ich jetzt nicht da, so will ich noch einmal antworten.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Sie haben hoffentlich nichts dagegen, da&szlig; ich diesen Brief als Antworttype bei anderen, gleichen Anfragen wie &quot;Wo kann ich als normalverdienender Mensch ein Hundertwasser-Original erwerben?&quot; verwende.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt da verschiedenste Aspekte. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die direkteste Antwort ist: &quot;Normalverdienende&quot; kaufen sich Autos und fahren damit herum, obwohl es umweltfreundlicher und billiger w&auml;re, Fahrrad, Bahn, Autobus zu ben&uuml;t&shy;zen. Millionen von Autos werden von Normalverdienenden erworben auf Raten, auf Kredit. Die Preise sind &auml;hnlich - nur verschlechtert sich der Zustand der Autos. Ein Bild erm&ouml;g&shy;licht eine gr&ouml;&szlig;ere Reise in sch&ouml;nere Welten.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein anderer Aspekt: Will man ein Bild wegen seines ideellen oder finan&shy;ziellen Wertes? Ich selbst bin Sammler von Kunstwerken, mit denen ich sehr gl&uuml;ck&shy;lich bin. Ich nehme meine Sammlung &uuml;berall mit auf meinen Reisen. Ich habe alle meine Lieblinge dabei: Bonnard, Rousseau, Schiele, Klimt, Paolo Ucello, Les tr&eacute;s riches heures du Duc de Berry, B&ouml;cklin (Die Toteninsel), van Gogh, Kumpf, Gauguin, Dix, Brueg&shy;hel, Caspar David Friedrich, indische Miniatu&shy;ren und viele, viele mehr.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Meine Postkartensammlung ist teilweise schon abge&shy;griffen vom vielen Anschauen. Einige sind schwer zu bekommen. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;berall wo ich bin, in Paris, Venedig, Wien, Ameri&shy;ka, ist mein erster Weg in eine gute Buchhandlung, um meine Sammlung zu erweitern. In Oslo z. B. ent&shy;deckte ich Maler, die ich noch nicht kannte, auf Postkarten! J. C. Dahl und Harald Sohl&shy;berg z. B. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich sende Ihnen, lieber Freund, einige Exemplare meiner Sammlung, die ich sehr mag und doppelt habe. Von denen, die meine Lieblinge sind, kann ich mich nicht trennen. Aber vielleicht ist es doch ein Grundstock auch f&uuml;r Ihre Sammlung. Das Tolle daran ist, man kann tr&auml;umen, wo immer man sie zur Hand nimmt: in der Stra&szlig;enbahn, im Wartezimmer, im Ur&shy;laub. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein dritter Aspekt: Es war immer mein Ziel, m&ouml;g&shy;lichst vielen Menschen durch meine Kunst Freude zu machen. Um aber alle zufriedenzustellen, m&uuml;&szlig;te ich Bilder am Flie&szlig;band produzieren, das immer schneller l&auml;uft, wie ein Maschinengewehr. Etwa 1000 Bilder t&auml;glich kann ich menschenunm&ouml;g&shy;lich schaffen, auch wenn ich sehr schnell male. (Jetzt sind es etwa vier bis sechs Bilder j&auml;hrlich, weil ich mehr und mehr architek&shy;to&shy;nisch besch&auml;ftigt bin). &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das hei&szlig;t, meine Bilder k&ouml;nnen nur billiger werden, wenn sie schlechter werden bzw. m&uuml;&szlig;te ich so viele &quot;pro&shy;duzieren&quot;, da&szlig; ich sie nicht mehr mit Herz und Seele f&uuml;llen kann. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist nicht m&ouml;glich, da&szlig; tausende Menschen Kinder von &lt;u&gt;einer&lt;/u&gt; Frau haben k&ouml;nnen, wenn diese Frau nur alle neun Monate ein Kind bekommen kann und sicher nicht mehr als zwanzig Mal.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Bilder malen ist ein sch&ouml;pferischer Akt, sogar ein schwieriger, weil er in allerh&ouml;chster Konzen&shy;tra&shy;tion, Hingabe, Ehrlichkeit, originaler Kreativi&shy;t&auml;t, Un&shy;wiederholbarkeit, mit Herz und in Harmonie mit der Sch&ouml;pfung der Natur - und das alles nicht intellektu&shy;ell, sondern &quot;unbewu&szlig;t&quot; -&nbsp; mit Gef&uuml;hl von&shy;statten geht. Das alles geht langsam vor sich, genauso wie ein Baum seine Zeit zum Wachsen braucht. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist fast so, als ob ich mich f&uuml;r den Wert meiner Bilder entschuldigen m&uuml;&szlig;te. Der finanzielle Wert entsteht aber auf dem freien Markt durch Angebot und Nachfrage, ohne da&szlig; ich das beeinflussen kann. Auch wenn ich Bilder verschenke, haben sie den gleichen Wert wie die Preise auf dem internationalen Kunst&shy;markt und auf Auktio&shy;nen. Es ist so wie der Wasser&shy;stand in kommunizieren&shy;den Gef&auml;&szlig;en.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Daher verkaufe ich schon seit drei&szlig;ig Jahren meine Bilder nicht mehr, sondern trage Sorge, da&szlig; sie in Museen und Galerien ausgestellt werden, wo sie von vielen Menschen gesehen werden k&ouml;nnen. Nur f&uuml;r eine Elite zu schaffen, die die Bilder &quot;f&uuml;r sich hat&quot; oder gar in Banksafes aufbewahrt, widerstrebt mir. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;brigens: Teure Kunstwerke ben&ouml;tigen teure Instal&shy;lationen, Sicherheit vor Einbr&uuml;chen, Alarmanlagen, &Uuml;berwachungsdienste und Klimaanlagen, Luftbefeuch&shy;tungsger&auml;te sowie S&auml;ure-, Hitze- und Trockenheit-Warnanlagen, d. h. der Besitzer eines Kunstwerkes tr&auml;gt Verantwortung wie f&uuml;r ein Kind.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ferner hat jedes Werk eine Oeuvre-Nummer und einen Akt mit Diapositi&shy;ven, Werdegang, Lebenslauf und Dokumentation und so etwas wie ein Identit&auml;tskon&shy;volut, genannt Certificat d&#039;authenticit&eacute;, in mehreren Sprachen. Inhalt des Zertifikats: Foto, Arbeitsgang&shy;fotos, Technik, Ma&szlig;e, Herstel&shy;lungsorte, Ausstel&shy;lungsverzeichnis, Reproduktionsliste, Sammlerliste (Bilder wechseln oft &uuml;ber zwanzig Mal den Besitzer), Si&shy;gna&shy;turvermerke, Besch&auml;&shy;digungen, Material&shy;herk&uuml;nfte, Konservierungshinweise, sowie Leihver&shy;pflichtung f&uuml;r Ausstellungen und Aus&shy;kunftverpflichtung im Falle des Besitzwechsels.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Daher bin ich seit f&uuml;nfundzwanzig Jahren mehr und mehr dazu &uuml;bergegangen, Graphiken und Reproduktionen so zu verfeinern und zu vervollkommnen, da&szlig; sie die Ori&shy;ginalbilder weit an Aussagekraft, Dichte und z. T. Haltbarkeit &uuml;ber&shy;tref&shy;fen.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die signierten Originalgraphiken sind eigenst&auml;ndige Werke in Mischtech&shy;nik, die nicht kopierbar sind und wo Techniken zum Tragen kommen, die in der Malerei nicht erreichbar sind, z. B. Metallpr&auml;gungen in vielen Farben, fluoreszierende und nachtleuchtende Farben, Farbtiefen durch Lasurtechniken und Glasper&shy;leneffekte. Da ich mich derart intensiv bem&uuml;h&shy;te, in der Repro&shy;duktion die Originale zu &uuml;bertreffen, fak&shy;tisch am Bild weiterzumalen, es zu vollenden, ist der Preis der Graphiken auch gestiegen und der der Reproduk&shy;tionen, schon allein durch die aufwendige, kompli&shy;zierte Drucktechnik in viel mehr Farben als &uuml;blich.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein anderer Aspekt: Es ist schon schlechter Wille oder aber nicht ideelles, sondern finanzielles In&shy;teresse, wenn jemand sagt, meine Bilder w&auml;ren un&shy;erschwinglich. Es gibt Bilder f&uuml;r jede B&ouml;rse; von Briefmarken zu &lt;u&gt;1 DM&lt;/u&gt;, die wahre Meisterwerke der Stechkunst sind (mit der Lupe zu betrachten) &uuml;ber die Postkarten, Reproduktionen in B&uuml;chern und Kalen&shy;dern, zu Postern und gro&szlig;formatigen Reproduktionen von hoher Qualit&auml;t, Originalgraphiken, Gobelins zu Bildern in Mischtechnik sind Werke in &lt;u&gt;jeder&lt;/u&gt; Preiska&shy;tegorie vorhanden.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein anderer Aspekt: Oft habe ich auf Briefe &auml;hnlich wie den Ihren mit Bilderschenkungen geantwortet. Die Briefe waren nur aggressiver, etwa so: &quot;Ich bin ein armer Student, ich liebe Deine Bilder, kann sie mir jedoch nicht lei&shy;sten. Du malst f&uuml;r die Kapita&shy;listen&shy;schweine. Willst du nicht auch ein Schwein sein, schenk mir ein Bild.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich habe es getan, mehrmals. Als ich drei Wochen sp&auml;ter den Mann besuchte, war das Bild verkauft. Er erkl&auml;r&shy;te mir: Da er sich ein Bild von mir zu erwerben nicht &lt;u&gt;leisten&lt;/u&gt; kann, so kann er es sich auch nicht &lt;u&gt;leisten&lt;/u&gt;, es zu behalten. Fast alle Schenkungen&nbsp; endeten so, ich glaube sogar 100%!&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das Bild mu&szlig;te verkauft werden, weil die Mutter oder die Frau an Krebs erkrankt w&auml;re und man Geld f&uuml;r die Operation gebraucht habe. Bild oder Leben. Leben geht vor. Oder Scheidung. Man h&auml;tte sich nicht eini&shy;gen k&ouml;nnen, wem das Bild geh&ouml;rt. Oder man h&auml;tte &lt;u&gt;sofort&lt;/u&gt; eine gr&ouml;&szlig;ere Geld&shy;summe aufbringen m&uuml;ssen, sonst w&auml;re das Haus gepf&auml;ndet worden und man s&auml;&szlig;e auf der Stra&szlig;e.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Oder man h&auml;tte eine Kaution erlegen m&uuml;ssen, damit jemand aus dem Gef&auml;ngnis k&auml;me. Oder so&shy;fort eine gro&szlig;e Geldsumme beschaffen, steuerfrei f&uuml;r einen Haus- oder Grundst&uuml;ckpreis. Morgen w&auml;re es zu sp&auml;t gewesen, etc. etc.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das alles und viel mehr habe ich schon erlebt. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Kei&shy;nes&lt;/u&gt; der geschenkten Bilder blieb unverkauft beim Beschenkten. Meist schon innerhalb von drei Wochen oder schon am n&auml;chsten Tag!&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein anderer Aspekt: Man soll Bilder kaufen, die man &lt;u&gt;liebt&lt;/u&gt;, solange sie nicht teuer sind. Die gro&szlig;en, ber&uuml;hmten Sammlungen von Veuillard, Kahnweiler, Guggenheim, und andere mehr mit Picassos, van Goghs etc., die jetzt hunderte Millionen kosten, wurden gro&szlig;teils fr&uuml;hzeitig f&uuml;r ein &lt;u&gt;Butter&shy;brot&lt;/u&gt; pro Bild erworben. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich selbst kann mich gut erinnern, da&szlig; ich 1950 - 1960 oft f&uuml;r ein But&shy;terbrot oder ein Abendessen oder einen Kaffee Bilder gegeben habe, vor lauter Freude, da&szlig; sich jemand f&uuml;r meine Arbeiten inter&shy;essiert hat. Picasso hatte nur eine Hose, als er sie in die Rei&shy;nigung bringen lie&szlig;, mu&szlig;te er im Bett bleiben, und ein Sammler hat die Hose f&uuml;r ihn ausge&shy;l&ouml;st.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt jetzt &lt;u&gt;viele&lt;/u&gt; unbekannte Maler, die besser sind als van Gogh oder ich, nur sind sie im Verbor&shy;genen. Auf Kunstausstellungen, manchmal sogar auf Auktionen und im Freundeskreis sind sie aber auf&shy;find&shy;bar und ganz billig zu haben so wie seinerzeit van Gogh und Gauguin, und das werden die ganz Gro&szlig;en der Zukunft.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch Bilder von Kindern k&ouml;nnen z. B. gerahmt jeden van Gogh in den Schatten stellen. Man mu&szlig; nur ein ganz klein wenig suchen. Sogar in Zeitungen finden sich oft Meisterwerke!&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die allergr&ouml;&szlig;te Genugtuung ist, selbst kreativ t&auml;tig zu sein und nicht passiv Kunst zu konsumieren. Sein eigenes Ich, seine eigenen Wurzeln kennen&shy;lernen. Wenn man die Welt durch die Augen anderer sieht, ist man nicht frei. Die Reise zu sich selbst ist endlos begl&uuml;&shy;ckend, und es ist auch die einzig m&ouml;gliche Reise, um als selb&shy;st&auml;n&shy;diges, individuelles, sch&ouml;pfe&shy;risches Wesen auf dieser Welt eine Daseinsberechti&shy;gung zu erlangen. Sonst ist und bleibt man Sklave, Spielball von kurzlebigen In&shy;teressen anderer.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es w&auml;re noch vieles zu sagen.&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_occasion_en-'&lt;p&gt;Written in Vienna in February 1995.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 729-732 (German and English)',
text_published_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln, 2002, S. 729-732 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_author-'Hundertwasser',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne, 2002',
text_source_en-'',
text_source_ge-'',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.1.2
object(text,'1.1.2','The Four Names',[
id-77,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-77,
txt-'1.1.2',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'The Four Names',
text_title_ge-'Die vier Namen',
text_keywords-'name, Hundertwasser, Friedensreich, Regentag, Dunkelbunt',
text_date-'2000-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;In 1949, at age 20, young Stowasser decided to take the name Hundertwasser. He had learned that the syllable &lt;em&gt;sto&lt;/em&gt; meant &lt;em&gt;hundred&lt;/em&gt; in Russian and other Slavonic languages and he changed his surname to its more poetic form, &ldquo;Hundertwasser&rdquo;. The new signature added to the paintings of this year, hesitatingly at first, sometimes in the abbreviated form &ldquo;Huwa&rdquo; or as a visual symbol: the number 100 with three wavy lines. For a long time, the Viennese critics were unwilling to recognise the new name Hundertwasser had given himself and continued to use the name Stowasser when referring to his paintings. Only much later did Hundertwasser learn that etymologically the name Stowasser is derived from Tyrolian dialect and really meant &lt;em&gt;standing water&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;He changed his first name to Friedereich while he was living in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Japan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; for a year in 1961 and wanted to find a way to transcribe his name into Japanese script, which is based on objects and concepts. Hundertwasser did not represent a problem and Friedrich was divided up into the signs for Friede (peace) and reich (realm). In 1968, he extended and clarified Friedereich &ndash; via the interim form Friedenreich, which can be seen on a few paintings from this period &ndash; to Friedensreich. His first and last names now had the same number of letters, 13, a type of magical numerology in which Hundertwasser believed and which, like a favourable omen, prophesies happiness for him as well as the people who viewed his works.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&rsquo;s world was an incomplete world, but one full of peace. Hundertwasser lived in a &ldquo;realm of peace&rdquo;, in a vegetative world. With him, everything revolved around the symbolic image of the plant, the peaceful cycle of its existence: the seed sinking into the ground &ndash; growing &ndash; budding &ndash; blossoming &ndash; wilting- withering &ndash; turning into humus, onto which a seed falls anew. This was a world without tragedy and cruelty. The animal world, based on the &ldquo;eat or be eaten&rdquo; principle, with its struggle for survival, its natural selection, was completely alien to Hundertwasser&rsquo;s philosophy and feelings. His was the world on the fourth day of Creation: &ldquo;and the earth brought forth grass, the herb yielding seeds and the tree yielding fruit; and there were lights in the firmament of the heaven to rule over the day and over the night and divide the light from the darkness.&rdquo; In such a world came man, created on the sixth day; not to have dominion over it, but to live in peace with it and all its creatures. But the elixir of life that made everything fertile was water: hence the name he chose to complement Hundertwasser and Friedensreich: Regentag.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;The third name, Regentag (Rainy Day), was the name he gave to his boat &ndash; and which the boat gave back to him. He identified more with his boat than he did with any of his houses &ndash; none of which became a permanent residence. Continually on the move, his restlessness found its most consistent expression in the Regentag. He was at home everywhere and nowhere when he was on board and completely at peace with himself.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;The Regentag had previously been an old salt-hauler which ran between &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Sicily&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;North Africa&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; and was originally called the Giuseppe T. Hundertwasser bought her in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Palermo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; in 1968 and sailed with her to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Venice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;. In the docks of Pellestrina, in the Venetian lagoon, he had her refurbished and gradually made her fit for navigation on the high seas. Hundertwasser painted his boat and gave her brightly coloured sails. He acquired a captain&rsquo;s licence and lived for months on board &ndash; as can be seen in the beautiful film made by Peter Schamoni. In 1976, the Regentag sailed to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;New Zealand&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;, where she found a permanent mooring in the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Bay&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Islands&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;. Hundertwasser was on board much of the way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;He decided on the name Regentag because &ldquo;on a rainy day the colours st&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;art &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;to shine. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;That&rsquo;s why to me a dreary day &ndash; a rainy day &ndash; is the most beautiful day. That&rsquo;s a day when I can work. When it rains I am happy. And when it rains I know my day has begun!&rdquo; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;From 1972 onwards, the name Regentag, cropped up in his paintings, not only as a designation of the place where the artist was painting; but also as a signature. In it, the person, place and time merged into a harmonious whole to which the completed work stood monument. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Regentag had created it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;The name Dunkelbunt (Dark-Bright) was the last to be added to the others, in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;New Zealand&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; in 1978. Like Regentag, Dunkelbunt was primarily connected with his understanding of colour. He called the person who produced a series of photographs of his New Zealand island paradise Dunkelbunt, as if he wanted to ascribe to him the the dusky light of an intermediate realm between anonymity identity &ndash; and made no secret of the fact that he himself was Dunkelbunt. Dunkelbunt photographed the Realm of Peace (Friedensreich), to which the Regentag had travelled and in which Hundertwasser painted: &ldquo;Dunkelbunt means: in pure, vibrant, radiantly deep colours, a little sad like on a rainy day.&rdquo; His four names therefore encapsulate his entire oeuvre.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;In 1949, at age 20, young Stowasser decided to take the name Hundertwasser. He had learned that the syllable &lt;em&gt;sto&lt;/em&gt; meant &lt;em&gt;hundred&lt;/em&gt; in Russian and other Slavonic languages and he changed his surname to its more poetic form, &ldquo;Hundertwasser&rdquo;. The new signature added to the paintings of this year, hesitatingly at first, sometimes in the abbreviated form &ldquo;Huwa&rdquo; or as a visual symbol: the number 100 with three wavy lines. For a long time, the Viennese critics were unwilling to recognise the new name Hundertwasser had given himself and continued to use the name Stowasser when referring to his paintings. Only much later did Hundertwasser learn that etymologically the name Stowasser is derived from Tyrolian dialect and really meant &lt;em&gt;standing water&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;He changed his first name to Friedereich while he was living in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Japan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; for a year in 1961 and wanted to find a way to transcribe his name into Japanese script, which is based on objects and concepts. Hundertwasser did not represent a problem and Friedrich was divided up into the signs for Friede (peace) and reich (realm). In 1968, he extended and clarified Friedereich &ndash; via the interim form Friedenreich, which can be seen on a few paintings from this period &ndash; to Friedensreich. His first and last names now had the same number of letters, 13, a type of magical numerology in which Hundertwasser believed and which, like a favourable omen, prophesies happiness for him as well as the people who viewed his works.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&rsquo;s world was an incomplete world, but one full of peace. Hundertwasser lived in a &ldquo;realm of peace&rdquo;, in a vegetative world. With him, everything revolved around the symbolic image of the plant, the peaceful cycle of its existence: the seed sinking into the ground &ndash; growing &ndash; budding &ndash; blossoming &ndash; wilting- withering &ndash; turning into humus, onto which a seed falls anew. This was a world without tragedy and cruelty. The animal world, based on the &ldquo;eat or be eaten&rdquo; principle, with its struggle for survival, its natural selection, was completely alien to Hundertwasser&rsquo;s philosophy and feelings. His was the world on the fourth day of Creation: &ldquo;and the earth brought forth grass, the herb yielding seeds and the tree yielding fruit; and there were lights in the firmament of the heaven to rule over the day and over the night and divide the light from the darkness.&rdquo; In such a world came man, created on the sixth day; not to have dominion over it, but to live in peace with it and all its creatures. But the elixir of life that made everything fertile was water: hence the name he chose to complement Hundertwasser and Friedensreich: Regentag.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;The third name, Regentag (Rainy Day), was the name he gave to his boat &ndash; and which the boat gave back to him. He identified more with his boat than he did with any of his houses &ndash; none of which became a permanent residence. Continually on the move, his restlessness found its most consistent expression in the Regentag. He was at home everywhere and nowhere when he was on board and completely at peace with himself.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;The Regentag had previously been an old salt-hauler which ran between &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Sicily&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;North Africa&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; and was originally called the Giuseppe T. Hundertwasser bought her in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Palermo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; in 1968 and sailed with her to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Venice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;. In the docks of Pellestrina, in the Venetian lagoon, he had her refurbished and gradually made her fit for navigation on the high seas. Hundertwasser painted his boat and gave her brightly coloured sails. He acquired a captain&rsquo;s licence and lived for months on board &ndash; as can be seen in the beautiful film made by Peter Schamoni. In 1976, the Regentag sailed to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;New Zealand&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;, where she found a permanent mooring in the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Bay&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Islands&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;. Hundertwasser was on board much of the way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;He decided on the name Regentag because &ldquo;on a rainy day the colours st&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;art &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;to shine. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;That&rsquo;s why to me a dreary day &ndash; a rainy day &ndash; is the most beautiful day. That&rsquo;s a day when I can work. When it rains I am happy. And when it rains I know my day has begun!&rdquo; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;From 1972 onwards, the name Regentag, cropped up in his paintings, not only as a designation of the place where the artist was painting; but also as a signature. In it, the person, place and time merged into a harmonious whole to which the completed work stood monument. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Regentag had created it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;The name Dunkelbunt (Dark-Bright) was the last to be added to the others, in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;New Zealand&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; in 1978. Like Regentag, Dunkelbunt was primarily connected with his understanding of colour. He called the person who produced a series of photographs of his New Zealand island paradise Dunkelbunt, as if he wanted to ascribe to him the the dusky light of an intermediate realm between anonymity identity &ndash; and made no secret of the fact that he himself was Dunkelbunt. Dunkelbunt photographed the Realm of Peace (Friedensreich), to which the Regentag had travelled and in which Hundertwasser painted: &ldquo;Dunkelbunt means: in pure, vibrant, radiantly deep colours, a little sad like on a rainy day.&rdquo; His four names therefore encapsulate his entire oeuvre.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;1949, im Alter von zwanzig Jahren, entschied sich der junge Stowasser f&uuml;r den Namen Hundertwasser. Er erfuhr damals, da&szlig; die Silbe &bdquo;sto&ldquo; auf Russisch und in slawischen Sprachen &bdquo;hundert&ldquo; bedeutet, und verwandelte seinen Familiennamen in seine poetische Form &bdquo;Hundertwasser&ldquo;. Wir finden die neue Signatur zuerst z&ouml;gernd in die Bilder dieses Jahres gesetzt, zuweilen noch in der Kurzform &bdquo;Huwa&ldquo; oder als visuelles K&uuml;rzel, die Zahl 100 und drei Wellenlinien. Die Wiener Kritik wollte lange Zeit Hundertwasser den selbstgew&auml;hlten Namen nicht zugestehen und blieb dabei, nur von den Bildern eines gewissen Stowasser zu sprechen. Erst sehr viel sp&auml;ter erfuhr Hundertwasser, da&szlig; sich der Name Stowasser etymologisch aus dem Tiroler Dialekt herleitet und eigentlich &bdquo;Stauwasser&ldquo; (Stehwasser) bedeutet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Seinen Vornamen verwandelte Hundertwasser in &quot;Friedereich&quot;, als er 1961 ein Jahr lang in Japan lebte und es galt, seinen Namen in die von Dingen und Begriffen ausgehenden Schriftzeichen der Japaner zu transkribieren: &bdquo;Hundertwasser&ldquo; machte da keine Schwierigkeiten, und &bdquo;Friedrich&ldquo; wurde in die Zeichen f&uuml;r &bdquo;Friede&ldquo; und &bdquo;reich&ldquo; zerlegt. 1968 erweiterte und verdeutlichte er Friedereich - &uuml;ber das Zwischenspiel &bdquo;Friedenreich&ldquo;, das wir in einigen Bildern dieser Zeit finden - zu &bdquo;Friedensreich&ldquo;. Vor- und Zunamen bestehen jetzt aus genau der gleichen Anzahl von Buchstaben, n&auml;mlich 13 - eine Zahlenmagie, an die Hundertwasser glaubte und die ihm und den Betrachtern seiner Bilder, wie eine g&uuml;nstige Sternkonstellation Gl&uuml;ck verhei&szlig;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Der dritte Name, Regentag, ist der Name, dem er seinem Schiff gab - und den das Schiff ihm zur&uuml;ckgab. Mit keinem seiner Aufenthaltsorte &ndash; &bdquo;Wohnsitze&ldquo; wurden sie alle nicht &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &ndash; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;hat er sich so identifiziert wie mit seinem Schiff. In ihm fand sein unruhiges Unterwegsein den best&auml;ndigsten Ausdruck. Mit ihm war er &uuml;berall und nirgends zu Hause und dabei ganz bei sich selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Die Regentag war zuvor ein alter Salzfrachter, der zwischen Sizilien und Nordafrika verkehrte und urspr&uuml;nglich Giuseppe T hie&szlig;. Hundertwasser erwarb ihn 1968 in Palermo und segelte mit ihm nach Venedig. In der Werft von Pellestrina, in der Lagune von Venedig, lie&szlig; er ihn umbauen und schrittweise hochseet&uuml;chtig machen. Hundertwasser hat sein Schiff bemalt und mit bunten Segeln versehen. Er erwarb das Kapit&auml;nspatent und lebte monatelang auf dem Schiff - Peter Schamoni hat dar&uuml;ber einen sch&ouml;nen Film gedreht. 1976 segelte die Regentag nach Neuseeland, wo sie in der Bay of Islands ihren endg&uuml;ltigen Ankerplatz fand; Hundertwasser hat einen gro&szlig;en Teil der Reise selbst mitgemacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Auf den Namen Regentag kam er, weil &bdquo;an einem Regentag die Farben zu leuchten beginnen. Deswegen ist ein tr&uuml;ber Tag &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &ndash; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;ein Regentag &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &ndash; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;f&uuml;r mich der sch&ouml;nste Tag. Das ist ein Tag, an dem ich arbeiten kann. Wenn es regnet, bin ich gl&uuml;cklich. Und wenn es regnet, wei&szlig; ich, da&szlig; mein Tag beginnt!&ldquo; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Von 1972 an taucht der Name Regentag auf seinen Bildern nicht nur als Bezeichnung des Ortes auf, an dem der K&uuml;nstler gemalt hat, sondern mutiert zur Signatur. In ihr verschmelzen Person, Ort und Stunde zu einer gl&uuml;cklichen Einheit, von dem das vollendete Werk Zeugnis ablegt. Regentag hat es geschaffen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Den Namen &bdquo;Dunkelbunt&ldquo; hat Hundertwasser als letzten den anderen zugef&uuml;gt, 1978 in Neuseeland. Wie &bdquo;Regentag&ldquo; hat &bdquo;Dunkelbunt&ldquo; vor allem mit seinem Verst&auml;ndnis der Farben zu tun. Den Urheber einer Serie von Fotos seines neuseel&auml;ndischen Inselparadieses bezeichnete er als &bdquo;Dunkelbunt&ldquo;, als wollte er ihm das D&auml;mmerlicht eines Zwischenreichs zwischen Anonymit&auml;t und Identifikation zuweisen &ndash; und l&auml;&szlig;t keinen Zweifel, da&szlig; er selbst dieser Dunkelbunt ist. Dunkelbunt fotografiert das Friedensreich, in das Regentag gereist ist und in dem Hundertwasser malte: &bdquo;Dunkelbunt bedeutet: in reinen starken leuchtend tiefen Farben, etwas trau&shy;rig wie an einem Regentag&ldquo;. So enthalten seine vier Namen das ganze Werk.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'',
text_author-'Wieland Schmied',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'&nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Personality, Life, Work. Taschen, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Cologne&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;, 2000, p. 35&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;',
text_source_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser 1928-2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Pers&ouml;nlichkeit, Leben, Werk. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2000, S. 35&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

