object(text,'1.1.2.1','The name Hundertwasser',[
id-29,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-29,
txt-'1.1.2.1',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'The name Hundertwasser',
text_title_ge-'Der Name Hundertwasser',
text_keywords-'Hundertwasser',
text_date-'2000-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'In 1949, at age of 20, young Stowasser decided to take the name Hundertwasser. He had learned that the syllable &lt;em&gt;sto&lt;/em&gt; meant &lt;em&gt;hundred&lt;/em&gt; in Russian and other Slavonic languages and he changed his surname to its more poetic form, &ldquo;Hundertwasser&rdquo;. The new signature was added to the paintings of this year, hesitatingly at first, sometimes in the abbreviated form &ldquo;Huwa&rdquo; or as a visual symbol: the number 100 with three wavy lines. For a long time, the Viennese critics were unwilling to recognise the new name Hundertwasser had given himself and continued to use the name Stowasser when referring to his paintings. Only much later did Hundertwasser learn that etymologically the name Stowasser is derived from Tyrolian dialect and really meant &lt;em&gt;standing water&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;',
text_contents_en-'In 1949, at age of 20, young Stowasser decided to take the name Hundertwasser. He had learned that the syllable &lt;em&gt;sto&lt;/em&gt; meant &lt;em&gt;hundred&lt;/em&gt; in Russian and other Slavonic languages and he changed his surname to its more poetic form, &ldquo;Hundertwasser&rdquo;. The new signature was added to the paintings of this year, hesitatingly at first, sometimes in the abbreviated form &ldquo;Huwa&rdquo; or as a visual symbol: the number 100 with three wavy lines. For a long time, the Viennese critics were unwilling to recognise the new name Hundertwasser had given himself and continued to use the name Stowasser when referring to his paintings. Only much later did Hundertwasser learn that etymologically the name Stowasser is derived from Tyrolian dialect and really meant &lt;em&gt;standing water&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;1949, im Alter von zwanzig Jahren, entschied sich der junge Stowasser f&uuml;r den Namen Hundertwasser. Er erfuhr damals, da&szlig; die Silbe &bdquo;sto&ldquo; auf Russisch und in slawischen Sprachen &bdquo;hundert&ldquo; bedeutet, und verwandelte seinen Familiennamen in seine poetische Form &bdquo;Hundertwasser&ldquo;. Wir finden die neue Signatur zuerst z&ouml;gernd in die Bilder dieses Jahres gesetzt, zuweilen noch in der Kurzform &bdquo;Huwa&ldquo; oder als visuelles K&uuml;rzel, die Zahl 100 und drei Wellenlinien. Die Wiener Kritik wollte lange Zeit Hundertwasser den selbstgew&auml;hlten Namen nicht zugestehen und blieb dabei, nur von den Bildern eines gewissen Stowasser zu sprechen. Erst sehr viel sp&auml;ter erfuhr Hundertwasser, da&szlig; sich der Name Stowasser etymologisch aus dem Tiroler Dialekt herleitet und eigentlich &bdquo;Stauwasser&ldquo; (Stehwasser) bedeutet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_author-'Wieland Schmied',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Vol. I:&nbsp;Personality, Life, Work. Taschen: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Cologne&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;, 2000, p. 35 &lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_source_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser 1928-2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Pers&ouml;nlichkeit, Leben, Werk. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2000, S. 35&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.1.2.2
object(text,'1.1.2.2','The Name Friedensreich',[
id-31,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-31,
txt-'1.1.2.2',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'The Name Friedensreich',
text_title_ge-'Der Name Friedensreich ',
text_keywords-'Friedensreich, Friedereich, Friedenreich',
text_date-'2000-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;div&gt;Hundertwasser changed his first name to Friedereich while he was living in Japan for a year in 1961 and wanted to find a way to transcribe his name into Japanese script, which is based on objects and concepts. Hundertwasser did not represent a problem and Friedrich was divided up into the signs for &lt;em&gt;Friede&lt;/em&gt; (peace) and &lt;em&gt;reich&lt;/em&gt; (realm). In 1968, he extended and clarified Friedereich &ndash; via the interim form Friedenreich, which can be seen on a few paintings from this period &ndash; to Friedensreich. His first and last names now had the same number of letters, 13, a type of magical numerology in which Hundertwasser believed and which, like a favourable omen, prophesied happiness for him as well as the people who viewed his works.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;Hundertwasser changed his first name to Friedereich while he was living in Japan for a year in 1961 and wanted to find a way to transcribe his name into Japanese script, which is based on objects and concepts. Hundertwasser did not represent a problem and Friedrich was divided up into the signs for &lt;em&gt;Friede&lt;/em&gt; (peace) and &lt;em&gt;reich&lt;/em&gt; (realm). In 1968, he extended and clarified Friedereich &ndash; via the interim form Friedenreich, which can be seen on a few paintings from this period &ndash; to Friedensreich. His first and last names now had the same number of letters, 13, a type of magical numerology in which Hundertwasser believed and which, like a favourable omen, prophesied happiness for him as well as the people who viewed his works.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Seinen Vornamen verwandelte Hundertwasser in &quot;Friedereich&quot;, als er 1961 ein Jahr lang in Japan lebte und es galt, seinen Namen in die von Dingen und Begriffen ausgehenden Schriftzeichen der Japaner zu transkribieren: &bdquo;Hundertwasser&ldquo; machte da keine Schwierigkeiten, und &bdquo;Friedrich&ldquo; wurde in die Zeichen f&uuml;r &bdquo;Friede&ldquo; und &bdquo;reich&ldquo; zerlegt. 1968 erweiterte und verdeutlichte er Friedereich - &uuml;ber das Zwischenspiel &bdquo;Friedenreich&ldquo;, das wir in einigen Bildern dieser Zeit finden - zu &bdquo;Friedensreich&ldquo;. Vor- und Zunamen bestehen jetzt aus genau der gleichen Anzahl von Buchstaben, n&auml;mlich 13 - eine Zahlenmagie, an die Hundertwasser glaubte und die ihm und den Betrachtern seiner Bilder, wie eine g&uuml;nstige Sternkonstellation Gl&uuml;ck verhei&szlig;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_author-'Wieland Schmied',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'&nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928-2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Personality, Life, Work. Taschen: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Cologne&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;, 2000, p. 35 &lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_source_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser 1928-2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Pers&ouml;nlichkeit, Leben, Werk. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2000, S. 35&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

