object(text,'1.1.2.3','The Name Regentag',[
id-33,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-33,
txt-'1.1.2.3',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'The Name Regentag',
text_title_ge-'Der Name Regentag',
text_keywords-'Regentag',
text_date-'2000-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'The third name, Regentag (rainy Day), was the name Hundertwasser gave to his boat &ndash; and which the boat gave back to him. He identified more with his boat than he did with any of his houses &ndash; none of which became a permanent residence. Continually on the move, his restlessness found its most consistent expression in the Regentag. He was at home everywhere and nowhere when he was on board and completely at peace with himself.&lt;br /&gt;The Regentag had previously been an old salt-hauler which ran between Sicily and North Africa and was originally called the Giuseppe T. Hundertwasser bought her in Palermo in 1968 and sailed with her to Venice. In the docks of Pellestrina, in the Venetian lagoon, he had her refurbished and gradually made her fit for navigation on the high seas. Hundertwasser painted his boat and gave her brightly coloured sails. He acquired a captain&rsquo;s licence and lived for months on board &ndash; as can be seen in the beautiful film made by Peter Schamoni. In 1976, the Regentag sailed to New Zealand, where she found a permanent mooring in the Bay of Islands. Hundertwasser was on board much of the way.&lt;br /&gt;Hundertwasser decided on the name Regentag because &ldquo;&lt;em&gt;on a rainy day the colours start to shine. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;That&rsquo;s why to me a dreary day &ndash; a rainy day &ndash; is the most beautiful day. That&rsquo;s a day when I can work. When it rains I am happy. And when it rains I know my day has begun!&lt;/em&gt;&rdquo; &lt;br /&gt;From 1972 onwards, the name Regentag, cropped up in his paintings, not only as a designation of the place where the artist was painting; but also as a signature. In it, the person, place and time merged into a harmonious whole to which the completed work stood monument. Regentag had created it.&lt;br /&gt;',
text_contents_en-'The third name, Regentag (rainy Day), was the name Hundertwasser gave to his boat &ndash; and which the boat gave back to him. He identified more with his boat than he did with any of his houses &ndash; none of which became a permanent residence. Continually on the move, his restlessness found its most consistent expression in the Regentag. He was at home everywhere and nowhere when he was on board and completely at peace with himself.&lt;br /&gt;The Regentag had previously been an old salt-hauler which ran between Sicily and North Africa and was originally called the Giuseppe T. Hundertwasser bought her in Palermo in 1968 and sailed with her to Venice. In the docks of Pellestrina, in the Venetian lagoon, he had her refurbished and gradually made her fit for navigation on the high seas. Hundertwasser painted his boat and gave her brightly coloured sails. He acquired a captain&rsquo;s licence and lived for months on board &ndash; as can be seen in the beautiful film made by Peter Schamoni. In 1976, the Regentag sailed to New Zealand, where she found a permanent mooring in the Bay of Islands. Hundertwasser was on board much of the way.&lt;br /&gt;Hundertwasser decided on the name Regentag because &ldquo;&lt;em&gt;on a rainy day the colours start to shine. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;That&rsquo;s why to me a dreary day &ndash; a rainy day &ndash; is the most beautiful day. That&rsquo;s a day when I can work. When it rains I am happy. And when it rains I know my day has begun!&lt;/em&gt;&rdquo; &lt;br /&gt;From 1972 onwards, the name Regentag, cropped up in his paintings, not only as a designation of the place where the artist was painting; but also as a signature. In it, the person, place and time merged into a harmonious whole to which the completed work stood monument. Regentag had created it.&lt;br /&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Der dritte Name, Regentag, ist der Name, dem er seinem Schiff gab &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&ndash; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; und den das Schiff ihm zur&uuml;ckgab. Mit keinem seiner Aufenthaltsorte &ndash; &bdquo;Wohnsitze&ldquo; wurden sie alle nicht &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&ndash; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;hat er sich so identifiziert wie mit seinem Schiff. In ihm fand sein unruhiges Unterwegsein den best&auml;ndigsten Ausdruck. Mit ihm war er &uuml;berall und nirgends zu Hause und dabei ganz bei sich selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Die Regentag war zuvor ein alter Salzfrachter, der zwischen Sizilien und Nordafrika verkehrte und urspr&uuml;nglich Giuseppe T hie&szlig;. Hundertwasser erwarb ihn 1968 in Palermo und segelte mit ihm nach Venedig. In der Werft von Pellestrina, in der Lagune von Venedig, lie&szlig; er ihn umbauen und schrittweise hochseet&uuml;chtig machen. Hundertwasser hat sein Schiff bemalt und mit bunten Segeln versehen. Er erwarb das Kapit&auml;nspatent und lebte monatelang auf dem Schiff &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&ndash; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; Peter Schamoni hat dar&uuml;ber einen sch&ouml;nen Film gedreht. 1976 segelte die Regentag nach Neuseeland, wo sie in der Bay of Islands ihren endg&uuml;ltigen Ankerplatz fand; Hundertwasser hat einen gro&szlig;en Teil der Reise selbst mitgemacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Auf den Namen Regentag kam er, weil &bdquo;an einem Regentag die Farben zu leuchten beginnen. Deswegen ist ein tr&uuml;ber Tag &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&ndash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; ein Regentag &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&ndash; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;f&uuml;r mich der sch&ouml;nste Tag. Das ist ein Tag, an dem ich arbeiten kann. Wenn es regnet, bin ich gl&uuml;cklich. Und wenn es regnet, wei&szlig; ich, da&szlig; mein Tag beginnt!&ldquo; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Von 1972 an taucht der Name Regentag auf seinen Bildern nicht nur als Bezeichnung des Ortes auf, an dem der K&uuml;nstler gemalt hat, sondern mutiert zur Signatur. In ihr verschmelzen Person, Ort und Stunde zu einer gl&uuml;cklichen Einheit, von dem das vollendete Werk Zeugnis ablegt. Regentag hat es geschaffen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_author-'Wieland Schmied',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Vol. I:&nbsp;Personality, Life, Work. Taschen: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Cologne&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;, 2000, p. 35 &lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_source_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser 1928-2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Pers&ouml;nlichkeit, Leben, Werk. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2000, S. 35&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

