]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.1.3.1.2
object(text,'1.1.3.1.2','The Origin of the Spiral',[
id-82,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-82,
txt-'1.1.3.1.2',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'The Origin of the Spiral',
text_title_ge-'Der Ursprung der Spirale',
text_keywords-'Spiral, Tachism, Spirale, Tachismus',
text_date-'2000-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In an interview in 1961, Hundertwasser explained the origin of his spiral this way: &ldquo;My spiral resulted from my striving to attain goals slowly&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. Tachism had destroyed all forms. Confronted by this strange and unexplored landscape, it was necessary to give oneself new rules and forms. One of these forms alone is significant &ndash; the form which corresponds to the result which comes about when opposites begin to move. Their movement is the spiral.&rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In an interview in 1961, Hundertwasser explained the origin of his spiral this way: &ldquo;My spiral resulted from my striving to attain goals slowly&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. Tachism had destroyed all forms. Confronted by this strange and unexplored landscape, it was necessary to give oneself new rules and forms. One of these forms alone is significant &ndash; the form which corresponds to the result which comes about when opposites begin to move. Their movement is the spiral.&rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In einem Interview hat Hundertwasser 1961 den Ur&shy;sprung seiner Spirale so erl&auml;utert: &quot;Meine Spirale ist aus dem Streben geboren worden, Ziele langsam zu erreichen ... Der Tachismus hatte alle Formen zer&shy;st&ouml;rt. Mit dieser fremden und unerforschten Land&shy;schaft konfrontiert war es n&ouml;tig, sich selbst neue Regeln und Formen zu geben. Eine einzige dieser Formen ist von Bedeutung - die Form, die dem Ergeb&shy;nis entspricht, das entsteht, wenn sich Gegens&auml;tze zu bewegen beginnen. Ihre Bewegung ist die Spirale.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'',
text_author-'Wieland Schmied',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'&nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Personality, Life, Work. Taschen: Cologne, 2000, p. 65&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;',
text_source_ge-'    &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Pers&ouml;nlichkeit, Leben, Werk. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2000, S. 65&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.1.3.1.3
object(text,'1.1.3.1.3','Hundertwasser\'s Spiral',[
id-83,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-83,
txt-'1.1.3.1.3',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'Hundertwasser&#039;s Spiral',
text_title_ge-'Hundertwassers Spirale',
text_keywords-'spiral, vegetative, Tachism, automatism, iconography, Spirale, vegetativ, Tachismus, Automatismus, Ikonographie',
text_date-'2000-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&rsquo;s spiral gives growth something to hold on to and architecture the form of growth. It is the most illustrative embodiment of the &lt;em&gt;coincidentia oppositorum&lt;/em&gt;. Thus, it can represent both: the structural aspect of the vegetative and organic housing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hundertwasser had an ambivalent relationship to Tachism: whereas he was attracted to the irregularity of the results, he mistrusted the spontaneity and occasional automatism of the processes which brought them about. His &ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Homage to Tachism&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&rdquo; shows how much he tried to assimilate from other styles in his development phase in the fifties in order to adopt and overcome them. And it shows how the spiral principle helped him to overcome what resisted him, what seemed alien to him, what he took to be an incumbrance, with the gentlest and tenderest of means: by embracing it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;All other motifs &ndash; apart from growth and building &ndash; with which Hundertwasser associated it in a later phase, are of subordinate rank and not an essential part of it: the spiral suns, the spiral trees, the spiral faces, the spiral spectacles &ndash; after all, the spiral can point to the most widely varying objects in Hundertwasser&rsquo;s iconography.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;1)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; coincidence of&nbsp; contradictions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&rsquo;s spiral gives growth something to hold on to and architecture the form of growth. It is the most illustrative embodiment of the &lt;em&gt;coincidentia oppositorum&lt;/em&gt;. Thus, it can represent both: the structural aspect of the vegetative and organic housing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hundertwasser had an ambivalent relationship to Tachism: whereas he was attracted to the irregularity of the results, he mistrusted the spontaneity and occasional automatism of the processes which brought them about. His &ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Homage to Tachism&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&rdquo; shows how much he tried to assimilate from other styles in his development phase in the fifties in order to adopt and overcome them. And it shows how the spiral principle helped him to overcome what resisted him, what seemed alien to him, what he took to be an incumbrance, with the gentlest and tenderest of means: by embracing it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;All other motifs &ndash; apart from growth and building &ndash; with which Hundertwasser associated it in a later phase, are of subordinate rank and not an essential part of it: the spiral suns, the spiral trees, the spiral faces, the spiral spectacles &ndash; after all, the spiral can point to the most widely varying objects in Hundertwasser&rsquo;s iconography.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;1)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; coincidence of&nbsp; contradictions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Hundertwassers Spirale gibt dem Wachstum Halt und der Architektur die Form von Wachstum. Sie ist die anschaulichste Verk&ouml;rperung der &lt;u&gt;coincidentia opposi&shy;torum&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;1)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. So kann sie beides gleichzeitig repr&auml;sentie&shy;ren: die Statik des Vegetativen und das organische Geh&auml;use.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Zum Tachismus hatte Hundertwasser ein ambivalentes Verh&auml;ltnis; w&auml;hrend ihn die Unregelm&auml;&szlig;igkeit der Resultate anzog, mi&szlig;traute er der Spontaneit&auml;t oder gar Automatik ihrer Entstehungsprozesse. Seine &lt;em&gt;Hom&shy;mage au Tachisme&lt;/em&gt;, 1961, zeigt, wieviel er sich in der Entwicklungsphase der f&uuml;nfziger Jahre von anderen Stilrichtungen anzueignen versuchte, um sie sich einzuverleiben und zu &uuml;berwinden. Und sie zeigt, wie ihm das Prinzip der Spirale half, das, was sich ihm entgegenstellte, was er als fremd empfand, was er als Hindernis begriff, mit den sanftesten und z&auml;rt&shy;lichsten Mitteln zu &uuml;berwinden: durch eine Umarmung.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Alle anderen Themen neben Wachstum und Bauwerk, mit denen Hundertwasser die Spirale in einer sp&auml;teren Phase verbindet, sind von untergeordnetem Rang und nicht wesentlich: die Spiralsonnen, die Spiralb&auml;ume, die Spiralgesichter, die Spiralbrillen. Innerhalb der Ikonographie Hun&shy;dertwassers kann die Spirale die verschiedensten Gegenstandshinweise aufnehmen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;1)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; Zusammenfall der Gegens&auml;tze &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'',
text_author-'Wieland Schmied',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Personality, Life, Work. Taschen: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;Cologne&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;, 2000, p. 67 &lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;',
text_source_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt&quot;&gt;Vol. I: Schmied, Wieland: Pers&ouml;nlichkeit, Leben, Werk. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2000, S. 67&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.1.3.2
object(text,'1.1.3.2','Hundertwasser\'s Painting Techniques',[
id-67,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-67,
txt-'1.1.3.2',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'Hundertwasser&#039;s Painting Techniques',
text_title_ge-'Hundertwassers Maltechiken',
text_keywords-'painting, technique, material, watercolour, paper, oil, PVA, linen, canvas, fibreboard, priming, egg tempera, mixed media, Malerei, Technik, Material, Aquarell, Papier, &Ouml;l, Leinen, Leinwand, Pre&szlig;faserplatte, Pressfaserplatte, Grundierung, Eitempera, Mischtechnik',
text_date-'1963-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Watercolours on white-primed, irregularly cut, torn and wrinkled pieces of wrapping paper which were often folded while in progress. The white ground is at first chalk/zinc white/bone glue, then usually the French commercial brand &ldquo;Casearti&rdquo; and since 1958 chalk/zinc white/polyvinyl acetate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Watercolours on drawing paper. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;As watercolours are considered in the Romance-language countries to be inferior to oil paintings, watercolours were mounted on canvas or other material, on wedged stretchers and sometimes even varnished, usually without my knowledge and against my will, to make them look like &ldquo;oil paintings&rdquo;. I must sternly warn about this, for watercolours which have been mistreated in this way do not increase in value, they decrease, because their watercolour quality is lost; the subsequent pasting damages the watercolour layer; and the temptation to varnish this &ldquo;painting on wedged stretchers&rdquo; is obvious. But once a watercolour has been varnished, the watercolours lose their characteristic matte charm, they get darker and take on an ugly brownish-yellow sheen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The irregularly torn or cut edges of my watercolours are often painted with more care than the rest of the picture and frequently constitute the true core of the work. Unfortunately, I found to my horror that the irregular edges of the watercolours were often cut to form a rectangle, usually during the paste-on process described above, or they were folded over the edges of the wedged stretchers and nailed down. Significant portions of the watercolours were destroyed in the process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Should it be absolutely necessary to mount a watercolour in order to preserve it, it should only be done with water-soluble paste on canvas and without cutting or bending back the irregular edges. The new ground must go beyond the outermost corners of the irregular edges of the watercolour. All notations on the back of the watercolour must, in the interest of everybody, be transferred to the new reverse side. If watercolour paint should flake off, together with poorly pasted ground, it will probably be necessary to fix these patches, sometimes even with varnish; but this task, as well as the mounting of watercolours, should be done by specialised restorers and not by frame-makers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Oil diluted with turpentine on fibreboard panels or wood with chalk/zinc white/glue ground.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Oil on canvas or cotton fabric with absorptive ground.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;All of these oil paintings are very lean and should be varnished in a few years, if possible with wax dissolved in turpentine, in order to preserve their matte character.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Oil on canvas with oil ground.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mixed media &ndash; watercolour base, tempera, oil &ndash; on wrapping paper or sometimes drawing paper which was mounted on hemp or canvas by me &ldquo;before starting work&rdquo;, without a press, and grounded with chalk, zinc white and glue.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;These paintings should not be confused with watercolours which were subsequently pasted onto canvas, stretched and varnished, turning them into bogus oil paintings.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Here paper has been inserted between canvas and chalk ground to bolster the canvas and thus create a perfect paint ground which is as durable, but not as heavy, as a wooden ground. Wrapping paper and stretched hemp are so strongly intermeshed using the teeth of a comb that they form a unified ground. The strong sweeping movement towards the edge enlarged the paper&rsquo;s surface by 5 %. For glue I have been using polyvinyl acetate and cellulose since 1958; before that it was bone glue, or gelatin. This surface, primed white with chalk, zinc white and polyvinyl acetate, is water-resistant and tight as a drum at the beginning of work, reminiscent of the freshly white-washed wall of a farmhouse. I can paint on it with any technique: oil, tempera, watercolour, synthetic binders, paste, rubber, resin, cheese, honey, always in the right sequence, of course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Grounds prepared in this way can be detached from the frame and transported rolled up with the image &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;However, the paper in the ground makes these pictures hygroscopic, i. e., they should not be exposed to fluctuations in the humidity. It is thus absolutely necessary with these paintings that the central heating have plenty of water, since a painting which is too dry and stretched too tautly can warp the canvas stretcher or even come undone. On the back of the canvas stretcher a diagonal wooden cross must be mounted to strengthen it. But if the humidity is too high the paintings sag.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In order to permanently preserve the radiance and matte sheen of a tempera picture, it should not be varnished until a few years later, and only with beeswax dissolved in turpentine, after removing dust with soft bread.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mixed media on canvas or canvas with silk or nylon pasted on it, always with a chalk/zinc white/glue ground. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mixed media on wood fibre board or wood with white absorptive ground.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Unfortunately I painted a few works in mixed media, nos. 311, 313&ndash;316, on cardboard I made myself. This material was made by pasting several layers of paper over a stretcher. These pictures are extremely sensitive to shock and warp when the air is too dry, which can even make the cardboard come undone.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Another big mistake I made was to cover some oil grounds with a chalk ground with glue, casein, egg or polyvinyl acetate and then paint with tempera or mixed media. The danger of pieces of the paint layers coming off, together with the chalk ground, is particularly great when jolted.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I prepare my tempera myself, with chicken egg, condensed linseed oil, dammar varnish, wax and paints in powder form.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I do not mix my paints, but apply them in pure form, one next to the other. I rarely overpaint.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I have been using nothing but light-resistant paints for six years now, i. e.: all earth colours, all cadmium colours, all cobalt colours, ultramarine, all viridian greens, malachite greens (applied separately) and cinnabar. But just the same, it is not good to expose a painting to bright light or extended sunlight.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Watercolours on white-primed, irregularly cut, torn and wrinkled pieces of wrapping paper which were often folded while in progress. The white ground is at first chalk/zinc white/bone glue, then usually the French commercial brand &ldquo;Casearti&rdquo; and since 1958 chalk/zinc white/polyvinyl acetate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Watercolours on drawing paper. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;As watercolours are considered in the Romance-language countries to be inferior to oil paintings, watercolours were mounted on canvas or other material, on wedged stretchers and sometimes even varnished, usually without my knowledge and against my will, to make them look like &ldquo;oil paintings&rdquo;. I must sternly warn about this, for watercolours which have been mistreated in this way do not increase in value, they decrease, because their watercolour quality is lost; the subsequent pasting damages the watercolour layer; and the temptation to varnish this &ldquo;painting on wedged stretchers&rdquo; is obvious. But once a watercolour has been varnished, the watercolours lose their characteristic matte charm, they get darker and take on an ugly brownish-yellow sheen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The irregularly torn or cut edges of my watercolours are often painted with more care than the rest of the picture and frequently constitute the true core of the work. Unfortunately, I found to my horror that the irregular edges of the watercolours were often cut to form a rectangle, usually during the paste-on process described above, or they were folded over the edges of the wedged stretchers and nailed down. Significant portions of the watercolours were destroyed in the process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Should it be absolutely necessary to mount a watercolour in order to preserve it, it should only be done with water-soluble paste on canvas and without cutting or bending back the irregular edges. The new ground must go beyond the outermost corners of the irregular edges of the watercolour. All notations on the back of the watercolour must, in the interest of everybody, be transferred to the new reverse side. If watercolour paint should flake off, together with poorly pasted ground, it will probably be necessary to fix these patches, sometimes even with varnish; but this task, as well as the mounting of watercolours, should be done by specialised restorers and not by frame-makers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Oil diluted with turpentine on fibreboard panels or wood with chalk/zinc white/glue ground.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Oil on canvas or cotton fabric with absorptive ground.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;All of these oil paintings are very lean and should be varnished in a few years, if possible with wax dissolved in turpentine, in order to preserve their matte character.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Oil on canvas with oil ground.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mixed media &ndash; watercolour base, tempera, oil &ndash; on wrapping paper or sometimes drawing paper which was mounted on hemp or canvas by me &ldquo;before starting work&rdquo;, without a press, and grounded with chalk, zinc white and glue.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;These paintings should not be confused with watercolours which were subsequently pasted onto canvas, stretched and varnished, turning them into bogus oil paintings.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Here paper has been inserted between canvas and chalk ground to bolster the canvas and thus create a perfect paint ground which is as durable, but not as heavy, as a wooden ground. Wrapping paper and stretched hemp are so strongly intermeshed using the teeth of a comb that they form a unified ground. The strong sweeping movement towards the edge enlarged the paper&rsquo;s surface by 5 %. For glue I have been using polyvinyl acetate and cellulose since 1958; before that it was bone glue, or gelatin. This surface, primed white with chalk, zinc white and polyvinyl acetate, is water-resistant and tight as a drum at the beginning of work, reminiscent of the freshly white-washed wall of a farmhouse. I can paint on it with any technique: oil, tempera, watercolour, synthetic binders, paste, rubber, resin, cheese, honey, always in the right sequence, of course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Grounds prepared in this way can be detached from the frame and transported rolled up with the image &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;However, the paper in the ground makes these pictures hygroscopic, i. e., they should not be exposed to fluctuations in the humidity. It is thus absolutely necessary with these paintings that the central heating have plenty of water, since a painting which is too dry and stretched too tautly can warp the canvas stretcher or even come undone. On the back of the canvas stretcher a diagonal wooden cross must be mounted to strengthen it. But if the humidity is too high the paintings sag.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In order to permanently preserve the radiance and matte sheen of a tempera picture, it should not be varnished until a few years later, and only with beeswax dissolved in turpentine, after removing dust with soft bread.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mixed media on canvas or canvas with silk or nylon pasted on it, always with a chalk/zinc white/glue ground. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mixed media on wood fibre board or wood with white absorptive ground.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Unfortunately I painted a few works in mixed media, nos. 311, 313&ndash;316, on cardboard I made myself. This material was made by pasting several layers of paper over a stretcher. These pictures are extremely sensitive to shock and warp when the air is too dry, which can even make the cardboard come undone.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Another big mistake I made was to cover some oil grounds with a chalk ground with glue, casein, egg or polyvinyl acetate and then paint with tempera or mixed media. The danger of pieces of the paint layers coming off, together with the chalk ground, is particularly great when jolted.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I prepare my tempera myself, with chicken egg, condensed linseed oil, dammar varnish, wax and paints in powder form.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I do not mix my paints, but apply them in pure form, one next to the other. I rarely overpaint.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I have been using nothing but light-resistant paints for six years now, i. e.: all earth colours, all cadmium colours, all cobalt colours, ultramarine, all viridian greens, malachite greens (applied separately) and cinnabar. But just the same, it is not good to expose a painting to bright light or extended sunlight.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Aquarelle auf wei&szlig; grundiertem, unregelm&auml;&szlig;ig geschnittenen, gerissenen und zerknitterten Packpapierst&uuml;cken, die w&auml;hrend der Arbeit oft gefaltet wurden. Der wei&szlig;e Grund ist zuerst Kreide-Zinkwei&szlig;-Knochenleim, dann meist das franz&ouml;sische Fabrikat &bdquo;Casearti&ldquo; und seit 1958 Kreide-Zinkwei&szlig;-Polyvinylacetat.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Aquarelle auf Zeichenpapier.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Da man in den lateinischen L&auml;ndern Aquarelle f&uuml;r minderwertiger als &Ouml;lbilder h&auml;lt, wurden, meist ohne da&szlig; ich darum wu&szlig;te und gegen meinen Willen, Aquarelle auf Leinen oder anderem Material aufgezogen, auf Keilrahmen gespannt und teilweise sogar gefirni&szlig;t, um so &bdquo;&Ouml;lbilder&ldquo; vorzut&auml;uschen. Ich mu&szlig; sehr davor warnen, denn derart zugerichtete Aquarelle gewinnen nicht, sondern verlieren an Wert, denn die Eigenschaft als Aquarell geht verloren, das nachtr&auml;gliche Aufkleben sch&auml;digt die Aquarellschicht, und die Versuchung, dieses &bdquo;Bild auf Keilrahmen&ldquo; zu firnissen liegt nahe. Wird ein Aquarell jedoch gefirni&szlig;t, so verlieren die Wasserfarben ihren matten charakteristischen Reiz, werden dunkel und h&auml;&szlig;lich br&auml;unlichgelb gl&auml;nzend.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Der unregelm&auml;&szlig;ig gerissene oder geschnittene Rand meiner Aquarelle ist oft mit gr&ouml;&szlig;erer Sorgfalt bemalt als das &Uuml;brige und bildet oft das wahre Zentrum des Bildes. Leider mu&szlig;te ich zu meinem Entsetzen feststellen, da&szlig;, meist beim vorherbeschriebenen Aufkleben, die unregelm&auml;&szlig;igen R&auml;nder der Aquarelle oft rechteckig zugeschnitten oder &uuml;ber die Kanten eines Keilrahmens gebogen und angenagelt worden sind. Bedeutende Teile der Aquarelle wurden so vernichtet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Falls zur Erhaltung es unbedingt notwendig sein sollte, ein Aquarell aufzuziehen, so nur mit wasserl&ouml;slichem Leim auf Leinen und so, da&szlig; der unregelm&auml;&szlig;ige Rand weder beschnitten noch umgebogen wird. Der neue Untergrund mu&szlig; bis &uuml;ber die letzten Winkel des unregelm&auml;&szlig;igen Aquarellrandes reichen. Alle Aufschriften der Aquarellr&uuml;ckseite m&uuml;ssen, im Interesse aller, auf die neue R&uuml;ckseite &uuml;bertragen werden. Wenn Farbe samt schlecht geleimtem Grund bei Aquarellen abbl&auml;ttern sollte, so ist es wohl notwendig die betreffenden Stellen zu binden, manchmal auch mit Firnis, jedoch mu&szlig; diese Arbeit, wie auch das Aufziehen von Aquarellen, durch spezialisierte Restauratoren und nicht durch Rahmentischler erfolgen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&Ouml;l mit Terpentin verd&uuml;nnt auf Pre&szlig;faserplatten oder Holz mit Kreide &ndash; Zinkwei&szlig; &ndash; Leim-Grund.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&Ouml;l auf Leinen oder Baumwolle mit saugendem Grund.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Alle diese &Ouml;lbilder sind sehr mager und sollten in einigen Jahren gefirni&szlig;t werden, wom&ouml;glich mit Wachs in Terpentin gel&ouml;st, um den matten Charakter zu erhalten.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&Ouml;l auf Leinen mit &Ouml;lgrund.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mischtechnik &ndash; Aquarelluntermalung, Eitempera, &Ouml;l &ndash; auf Packpapier oder manchmal Zeichenpapier, das &bdquo;vor Arbeitsbeginn&ldquo; von mir selbst ohne Presse auf Jute oder Leinwand aufgezogen und mit Kreide, Zinkwei&szlig; und Leim grundiert wurde.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Diese Bilder sind nicht mit Aquarellen zu verwechseln, die nachtr&auml;glich aufgeklebt, aufgespannt, gefirni&szlig;t und so in falsche &Ouml;lbilder verwandelt wurden.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hier befindet sich Papier zwischen Leinwand und Kreidegrund, um die Leinwand zu verst&auml;rken und so einen perfekten Malgrund zu erzielen, der so widerstandsf&auml;hig, jedoch nicht so schwer wie ein Holzgrund ist. Packpapier und aufgespannte Jute werden mit den Z&auml;hnen eines Kammes so stark ineinander getrieben, da&szlig; sie eine Einheit bilden. Durch die starken Streichbewegungen zum Rand hin wurde die Papierfl&auml;che bis zu 5% vergr&ouml;&szlig;ert. Als Leim verwende ich seit 1958 Polyvinylacetat und Celluloseleim, vorher Knochenleim. Diese mit Kreide, Zinkwei&szlig; und Polyvinylacetat grundierte wei&szlig;e Fl&auml;che ist wasserfest und zu Arbeitsbeginn wie eine Trommel gespannt und erinnert an eine frisch mit Kalk get&uuml;nchte Bauernhauswand. Ich kann darauf mit allen Techniken malen: &Ouml;l, Ei, Wasserfarben, synthetische Bindemittel, Leim, Gummi, Harz, K&auml;se, Honig, bei Beachtung der Reihenfolge selbstverst&auml;ndlich.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;So pr&auml;parierte Gr&uuml;nde k&ouml;nnen vom Rahmen abgenommen und mit dem Bild &bdquo;nach au&szlig;en&ldquo; gerollt transportiert werden.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Durch das Vorhandensein von Papier im Grund werden diese Bilder jedoch hygroscopisch, d. h. sie sollen nicht Luftfeuchtigkeitsver&auml;nderungen ausgesetzt werden. So ist es f&uuml;r diese Bilder absolut notwendig, die Zentralheizung mit Wasser zu versehen, da das zu sehr getrocknete und gespannte Bild den Blendrahmen werfen, ja sogar abspringen kann. Auf der R&uuml;ckseite des Blendrahmens mu&szlig; zur Verst&auml;rkung ein diagonales Holzkreuz verankert sein. Bei zu hoher Luftfeuchtigkeit jedoch erschlaffen die Bilder.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Um die Leuchtkraft und den Mattglanz des Temperabildes f&uuml;r immer zu erhalten, soll es erst in einigen Jahren und nur mit in Terpentin gel&ouml;stem Bienenwachs gefirni&szlig;t werden, wobei der Staub vorher mit weichem Brot entfernt wird.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mischtechnik auf Leinen oder mit Seide oder Nylon beklebtem Leinen, stets mit Kreide &ndash; Zinkwei&szlig; &ndash; Leim-Grund.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mischtechnik auf Holzfaserplatte oder Holz wei&szlig; saugend grundiert.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Ich habe leider einige Bilder in Mischtechnik auf selbstverfertigter Pappe gemalt. Dieser Karton entstand durch Aufkleben mehrerer Schichten Papier &uuml;ber einen Blendrahmen. Diese Bilder sind &auml;u&szlig;erst sto&szlig;empfindlich und werfen sich bei gro&szlig;er Trockenheit, wobei der ganze Karton abspringen kann.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Ein weiterer gro&szlig;er Fehler von mir war, da&szlig; ich leider einige &Ouml;lgr&uuml;nde mit einem Kreidegrund mit Leim, Kasein, Ei oder Polyvinylacetat &uuml;berzog und darauf mit Tempera oder Mischtechnik malte. Die Gefahr des Abspringens von Farbschichtst&uuml;cken samt Kreidegrund ist besonders bei Ersch&uuml;tterungen gro&szlig;. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Ich bereite meine Eitempera selbst mit H&uuml;hnerei, eingedicktem Lein&ouml;l, Dammarfirnis, Wachs und Pulverfarben.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Ich vermische meine Farben nicht, sondern trage sie rein und nebeneinander auf. Ich &uuml;bermale selten.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Seit sechs Jahren verwende ich nur mehr lichtechte Farben und zwar: alle Erdfarben, alle Kadmiumfarben, alle Kobaltfarben, Ultramarin, alle Chromgr&uuml;ne, Kupfergr&uuml;ne (f&uuml;r sich allein aufgetragen) und Zinnober. Trotzdem ist es nicht gut, ein Bild lange der Sonne oder starkem Licht auszusetzen.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Exhibition Catalogue &ldquo;Hundertwasser ist ein Geschenk f&uuml;r Deutschland&rdquo; (Hundertwasser Is a Gift to Germany). Galerie &Auml;nne Abels: Cologne, 1963&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 721-726 (German and English)&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Katalog der Ausstellung &bdquo;Hundertwasser ist ein Geschenk f&uuml;r Deutschland&ldquo;, Galerie &Auml;nne Abels, K&ouml;ln, 1963&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 721-726 (Deutsch und&nbsp;Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_author-'Hundertwasser',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'Courtesy Taschen, Cologne, 2002
',
