%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.1.3.3
object(text,'1.1.3.3','Letter on Colours',[
id-68,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-68,
txt-'1.1.3.3',
text_type-5,
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'Letter on Colours',
text_title_ge-'Brief &uuml;ber die Verwendung von Farben',
text_keywords-'painting, paint, technique, earth paint, Malerei, Farbe, Technik, Erdfarbe',
text_date-'1997-03-02',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Dear Helga P., &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Thank you for your letter, which reached me on the opposite side of the world.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The science of paint is very old and goes back to the Egyptians, even as far as cave painting. There are painting books from the Middle Ages, by Cellini &hellip; a few hundred years ago. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The best book on painting today is &ldquo;Das Malmaterial und seine &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Verwendung im Bilde&rdquo; (The Materials of the Artist and Their Use in Painting), by Max Doerner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Toxic paints have been used in painting from the oldest times: lead, cobalt, mercury, arsenic &ndash; lead for white, cobalt for blue and violet, mercury for red, arsenic for green (Paris green) and &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;verdigris.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Indian yellow was sheer cruelty to animals. Obtained from the urine of cows infected with jaundice. Now banned. Many &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;poisonous paints, still in common use 160 years ago, are now banned. If you buy artist&rsquo;s paints, of good quality &ndash; Schmincke, Windsor &amp; Newton, Rembrandt etc. &ndash; pay attention to the paint catalogue. In it the toxic content of each paint is listed. Children&rsquo;s school paints are non-toxic. Yet, they are not as durable. In modern times another toxicity has been added, however: the modern binders, solvents and varnishes. Formerly, linseed oil, genuine turpentine, bone and fish glues, flour paste, gum arabic, tempera made of fresh eggs, casein from curds, etc., were harmless; now, in contrast, one no longer knows what keeps the paint intact.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In case you don&rsquo;t care whether the paints are extremely bright or not, earth paints are highly recommended. There are red, &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;yellow, greenish soils, according to their clay or ferric oxide content. Also, coal (from bone and charcoal), chalk for white. And ultramarine is not poisonous, either. Earth paints, coal and chalk can even be eaten. Zinc oxide is also used as an ointment, as is ferruginous oxide, but not for wounds. As I said: toxic materials which are obtained from the earth, such as lead and cobalt, are also natural substances which &ldquo;return to earth&rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I like painting with pulverised earth best. Try pulverising a little bit of crumbling (soft) brick on a glass plate or white tile with one or two drops of water, using a flat pestle (available in paint supply shops) or the bottom of a glass or bottle (the bottom surface should be as flat as possible) and a spatula to scrape it together again. Once it&rsquo;s a fine powder, mix with water and &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;beaten egg (just one to three drops) and start painting!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In the meantime, cordially yours, &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;P S: Soil in various colours can be found on walks, by the road side, in quarries, bricks &hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;From a letter to Hundertwasser from Helga P., Dec. 12, 1996&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I have been painting for years, and for years I have had conscience pangs because the poison my paints contain is such a plague for the ground. &hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Now I have read a book about you, in which you &hellip; say you mix your paints yourself &hellip; from natural substances. Please tell me about your methods or any literature which describes this kind of paint preparation in more detail, for I don&rsquo;t know whom else I should ask about this.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Dear Helga P., &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Thank you for your letter, which reached me on the opposite side of the world.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The science of paint is very old and goes back to the Egyptians, even as far as cave painting. There are painting books from the Middle Ages, by Cellini &hellip; a few hundred years ago. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The best book on painting today is &ldquo;Das Malmaterial und seine &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Verwendung im Bilde&rdquo; (The Materials of the Artist and Their Use in Painting), by Max Doerner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Toxic paints have been used in painting from the oldest times: lead, cobalt, mercury, arsenic &ndash; lead for white, cobalt for blue and violet, mercury for red, arsenic for green (Paris green) and &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;verdigris.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Indian yellow was sheer cruelty to animals. Obtained from the urine of cows infected with jaundice. Now banned. Many &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;poisonous paints, still in common use 160 years ago, are now banned. If you buy artist&rsquo;s paints, of good quality &ndash; Schmincke, Windsor &amp; Newton, Rembrandt etc. &ndash; pay attention to the paint catalogue. In it the toxic content of each paint is listed. Children&rsquo;s school paints are non-toxic. Yet, they are not as durable. In modern times another toxicity has been added, however: the modern binders, solvents and varnishes. Formerly, linseed oil, genuine turpentine, bone and fish glues, flour paste, gum arabic, tempera made of fresh eggs, casein from curds, etc., were harmless; now, in contrast, one no longer knows what keeps the paint intact.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In case you don&rsquo;t care whether the paints are extremely bright or not, earth paints are highly recommended. There are red, &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;yellow, greenish soils, according to their clay or ferric oxide content. Also, coal (from bone and charcoal), chalk for white. And ultramarine is not poisonous, either. Earth paints, coal and chalk can even be eaten. Zinc oxide is also used as an ointment, as is ferruginous oxide, but not for wounds. As I said: toxic materials which are obtained from the earth, such as lead and cobalt, are also natural substances which &ldquo;return to earth&rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I like painting with pulverised earth best. Try pulverising a little bit of crumbling (soft) brick on a glass plate or white tile with one or two drops of water, using a flat pestle (available in paint supply shops) or the bottom of a glass or bottle (the bottom surface should be as flat as possible) and a spatula to scrape it together again. Once it&rsquo;s a fine powder, mix with water and &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;beaten egg (just one to three drops) and start painting!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In the meantime, cordially yours, &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;P S: Soil in various colours can be found on walks, by the road side, in quarries, bricks &hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;From a letter to Hundertwasser from Helga P., Dec. 12, 1996&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;I have been painting for years, and for years I have had conscience pangs because the poison my paints contain is such a plague for the ground. &hellip; Now I have read a book about you, in which you &hellip; say you mix your paints yourself &hellip; from natural substances. Please tell me about your methods or any literature which describes this kind of paint preparation in more detail, for I don&rsquo;t know whom else I should ask about this.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoBodyText&quot; style=&quot;line-height: normal&quot;&gt;Liebe Helga P., &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoBodyText&quot; style=&quot;line-height: normal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoBodyText&quot; style=&quot;line-height: normal&quot;&gt;danke f&uuml;r Ihren Brief, der mich am anderen Ende der Welt erreichte.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoBodyText&quot; style=&quot;line-height: normal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoBodyText&quot; style=&quot;line-height: normal&quot;&gt;Die Malfarbwissenschaft ist sehr alt und geht schon bis zu den &Auml;gyptern, ja H&ouml;hlenmalereien vor 25.000 Jahren zur&uuml;ck. Es gibt Malb&uuml;cher aus dem Mittelalter vom Malerm&ouml;nch Theophilus und von Cellini ... vor hunderten von Jahren. Das beste Malbuch heute ist &bdquo;Das Malmaterial und seine Verwendung im Bilde&ldquo; von Max Doerner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoBodyText&quot; style=&quot;line-height: normal&quot;&gt;Giftige Farben wurden seit Menschengedenken in der Malerei verwendet: Blei, Kobalt, Quecksilber, Arsen, Blei f&uuml;r Wei&szlig;, Kobalt f&uuml;r Blau und Violett, Quecksilber f&uuml;r Rot, Arsen f&uuml;r Gr&uuml;n (Schweinfurter Gr&uuml;n) und Gr&uuml;nspan.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Indisch-Gelb war reine Tierqu&auml;lerei! Aus dem Urin von mit Gelbsucht angesteckten K&uuml;hen gewonnen! Jetzt verboten. Viele giftige Farben, vor 160 Jahren &uuml;blich, sind jetzt verboten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoBodyText&quot; style=&quot;line-height: normal&quot;&gt;Wenn Sie K&uuml;nstlerfarben kaufen, von guter Qualit&auml;t, Schmincke, Windsor &amp; Newton, Rembrandt etc. - achten Sie auf den Farbkatalog! Da ist der Giftigkeitsgehalt jeder Farbe angegeben! Die Kinderfarben f&uuml;r Sch&uuml;ler sind &lt;u&gt;giftfrei&lt;/u&gt;! Allerdings nicht so haltbar.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In der modernen Zeit kommt jedoch eine andere Giftigkeit hinzu: die modernen Bindemittel, L&ouml;sungsmittel und Firnisse. Fr&uuml;her waren Lein&ouml;l, echter Terpentin, Knochen und Fischleime, Mehlkleister, Gummiarabicum, Eitempera aus frischen Eiern, Kasein aus Topfen etc. unbedenklich, jetzt hingegen wei&szlig; man nicht mehr, womit die Farben zusammengehalten werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Falls Sie auf keine stark leuchtenden Farben wertlegen, sind die Erdfarben sehr zu empfehlen. Es gibt rote, gelbe, gr&uuml;nliche Erden je nach Lehm- oder Eisenoxydgehalt. Ferner Kohle (aus Bein- und Holzkohle), Kreide f&uuml;r Wei&szlig;. Aber auch Ultramarin ist ungiftig. Erdfarben, Kohle, Kreide kann man sogar essen. Auch Zinkwei&szlig; wird f&uuml;r Salben verwendet, auch Eisenoxyd (Rost), jedoch nicht auf Wunden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Wie gesagt: Auch Giftstoffe, die aus der Erde gewonnen werden, wie Blei und Kobalt, sind nat&uuml;rliche Substanzen, die wieder &bdquo;in die Erde zur&uuml;ckgehen.&ldquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Ich male am liebsten mit zerriebener Erde. Probieren Sie einmal ein kleines St&uuml;ck morschen (weichen) Ziegel ... auf einer Glasplatte oder wei&szlig;en Kachel mit einem oder zwei Tropfen Wasser, mit einem flachen St&ouml;&szlig;el zu zerreiben (bekommt man im Farbgesch&auml;ft) oder mit der Unterseite eines Glases oder einer Flasche (die Unterseite soll m&ouml;glichst flach sein) und mit einem Spachtel zum wiederzusammenf&uuml;hren. Wenn ganz fein gerieben, mit Wasser, mit geschlagenem Ei (nur ein bis drei Tropfen) mischen und damit malen!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Herzlich inzwischen Ihr&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;2. M&auml;rz 1997 aus Neuseeland&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;P.S:: Erde in vielen Farben finden Sie beim Spazierengehen! Stra&szlig;enrand, Steinbruch, Ziegel....&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Aus dem Brief von Helga P. an Hundertwasser vom 30. 12. 1996&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Jahrelang male ich, und jahrelang plagen mich Gewissensbisse, weil das Gift, das in meinen Farben steckt, die Erde so plagt ... Nun lese ich ein Buch &uuml;ber Sie, in dem Sie .... sagen, Sie mischen Ihre Farben selber ... aus nat&uuml;rlichen Substanzen. Ich bitte Sie, mir Methoden oder Literatur anzugeben, die diese Art der Farbherstellung genauer beschreiben, weil ich nicht wei&szlig;, an wen sonst ich mich diesbez&uuml;glich wenden sollte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_occasion_en-'Written in New Zealand on 2 March 1997.&lt;br /&gt;',
text_occasion_ge-'Verfa&szlig;t in Neuseeland am 2. M&auml;rz 1997',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 44-45 (German and English)&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;/ Werkverzeichnis. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 44-45 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_author-'Hundertwasser',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'Courtesy Taschen Verlag, Cologne, 2002',
text_source_en-'',
text_source_ge-'',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.1.3.4
object(text,'1.1.3.4','On Hundertwasser\'s Youth work',[
id-84,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-84,
txt-'1.1.3.4',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'On Hundertwasser&#039;s Youth work',
text_title_ge-'Zu Hundertwassers Jugendwerk',
text_keywords-'Jugendwerk, youth work, Jugend, youth,
Kindheit, childhood',
text_date-'2004-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Amidst a more than turbulent, dangerous and life-threatening time in Vienna and environs during the final years of the war, he [Hundertwasser] nevertheless succeeded in fully immersing himself in the wonders available to him: a blossom, a postage stamp, the image on a postcard, the view out of the window of his room. In simple forms (round, bent, straight) and primary colors (yellow, green, red), the characteristics of objects, things, plants, trees, walls and murals etc. &mdash; situations in the world, in reality, which can be truly seen and experienced &mdash; are revealed to the youngster. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;From the amazingly precise ability of this child and youth to be completely immersed in what is visible and tactile among the world&rsquo;s infinitely rich miracles, the perceptions and attitudes which will determine Hundertwasser&rsquo;s later path in life and his artistic development are formed. These relatively simple concepts and constructs of his childhood help form his views and opinions about people, about the world and about nature. In this sense, Hundertwasser has remained true to the formative dreams of his childhood and youth throughout his life. &lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Amidst a more than turbulent, dangerous and life-threatening time in Vienna and environs during the final years of the war, he [Hundertwasser] nevertheless succeeded in fully immersing himself in the wonders available to him: a blossom, a postage stamp, the image on a postcard, the view out of the window of his room. In simple forms (round, bent, straight) and primary colours (yellow, green, red), the characteristics of objects, things, plants, trees, walls and murals etc. &mdash; situations in the world, in reality, which can be truly seen and experienced &mdash; are revealed to the youngster. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;From the amazingly precise ability of this child and youth to be completely immersed in what is visible and tactile among the world&rsquo;s infinitely rich miracles, the perceptions and attitudes which will determine Hundertwasser&rsquo;s later path in life and his artistic development are formed. These relatively simple concepts and constructs of his childhood help form his views and opinions about people, about the world and about nature. In this sense, Hundertwasser has remained true to the formative dreams of his childhood and youth throughout his life. &lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Inmitten einer mehr als turbulenten, gefahrvollen und lebensbedrohlichen Zeit damals in Wien und Umgebung w&auml;hrend der letzten Kriegsjahre, gelingt es ihm [Hundertwasser] dennoch, sich in die sich ihm darbietenden Wunder v&ouml;llig hingebungsvoll zu vertiefen: in eine Bl&uuml;te, in eine Briefmarke, in das Bild einer Postkarte, in den Anblick aus seinem Zimmerfenster. An den einfachen Formen (rund, gebogen, gerade) und an den prim&auml;ren Farben (gelb, gr&uuml;n, rot) erschlie&szlig;en sich dem Jugendlichen die Eigenschaften von Objekten, von Dingen, von Pflanzen, B&auml;umen, von Mauern und W&auml;nden usw., d. h. von den tats&auml;chlich sichtbaren und erfahrbaren Gegebenheiten der Welt, der Wirklichkeit.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Aus dieser erstaunlich pr&auml;zisen F&auml;higkeit des Kindes und Jugendlichen zu einer totalen Hingabe an die Sichtbarkeiten und an die Handhabbarkeiten der unendlich reichhaltigen Wunder der Welt entspringen in der Folge die Wahrnehmungen und Einstellungen, die Hundertwassers sp&auml;teren Lebensweg und k&uuml;nstlerische Entwicklung bestimmen werden. Es sind zudem auch die relativ einfachen Konzepte und Konstrukte der Kindheit, die seine Sichtweisen und Anschauungen &uuml;ber den Menschen, &uuml;ber die Welt und &uuml;ber die Natur mitformen. In diesem Sinn ist Hundertwasser ein Leben lang den pr&auml;genden Tr&auml;umen seiner Kindheit und seines Jugendalters treu geblieben.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'',
text_author-'Walter Schurian',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter, in: exhibition catalogue: Hundertwasser &ndash; Kunst &ndash; Mensch &ndash; Natur [Hundertwasser &ndash; Art &ndash; Man &ndash; Nature], Minoritenkloster, Tulln [Austria], 2004, p. 29.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;',
text_source_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter, in: Katalog der Ausstellung: Hundertwasser - Kunst - Mensch &ndash; Natur. Minoritenkloster, Tulln 2004, S. 29&lt;/p&gt;',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.1.4.0
object(text,'1.1.4.0','On Hundertwasser`s Graphic Work',[
id-18,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-18,
txt-'1.1.4.0',
text_type-'-1',
text_category-12,
text_title_en-'On Hundertwasser`s Graphic Work',
text_title_ge-'Zu Hundertwassers graphischem Werk',
text_keywords-'Graphik, graphic, graphic work, lithograph, silk screen, etching, colour woodcut, Lithographie, Siebdruck, Radierung, Farbholzschnitt',
text_date-'2002-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser mastered and innovated many graphic techniques, among them lithograph, silk screen, etching, colour woodcut and many others. He was one of the first to demand and practice complete transparency in terms of technique, dates of creation and editions for each sheet.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser never really created large editions of one and the same graphic work. His graphic editions comprise several colour versions and variants, which are not numbered separately, but instead numbered throughout the entire edition. It was his aim to make many different unique pieces within the art of the graphic, thereby going beyond machine production.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser always took great care to provide exact information about the work on each graphic sheet, in order to arrive at as complete a disclosure of a work&rsquo;s techniques and creation dates as possible.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;On the graphics can be found:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&rsquo;s signature (in manuscript or as Japanese inkan stamps),&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;date and place of the signature,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&oelig;uvre number,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;in many cases the name of the work,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;specimen number,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;listings or stamps and embossings of publishers, printers, paper and paint producers, or of the co-ordinators involved, and&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;colour-separation marks.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Many prints bear embossed, stamped or printed listings of colour variants, technical versions and edition sizes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;On the plates, on the stones or on the screens, additional signatures were often given, but also work numbers, and names, sometimes including the name of the originals, as well as place and date of creation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the case of many Japanese colour woodcuts the title of the work was printed in Japanese characters.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Occasionally Hundertwasser had the reverse of the graphic imprinted with all this information, and even went beyond that by listing the entire development and creative process of the print.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;In the catalogue of graphic work that was published in 1986, Walter Koschatzky put the graphics in chronological order by the date of print and introduced consecutive HWG (Hundertwasser Graphics) numbers.&lt;a name=&quot;_edn1&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;[1] &lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With the continuation of the graphic work after 1986, Hundertwasser&rsquo;s graphic oeuvre consists of 124 HWG numbers, counting the 23 doodle etchings as one number, namely HWG 124.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Portfolios as such were not assigned their own HWG number, because each graphic contained in a portfolio was given an HWG number.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As Walter Koschatzky explains in his introduction, Hundertwasser generally used oeuvre numbers to mark different types of graphics:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;- works that he created directly on the stone or plate, and that were therefore completely or predominantly made for this particular medium, are hence assigned a corresponding oeuvre number, for instance 940 &lt;em&gt;Bottlehousebath&lt;/em&gt;,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;- works transferred to a graphic medium from an existing painting or watercolour, that were reworked by him on plates or foils, and that are significantly different from the source work; these were also assigned their own oeuvre numbers. E. g. 699 &lt;em&gt;King Kong&lt;/em&gt;, after 202 &lt;em&gt;Kopf in zwei Perspektiven&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;em&gt;Head in Two Perspectives&lt;/em&gt;),&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;- works that were transferred to a graphic medium from an existing painting, watercolour or drawing, but corrected by the artist, changed in some details, and transferred to colour variants. Their numbers are those of the source work, and they received the addition A, B or C, e.g. 484A &lt;em&gt;Houses in Rain of Blood&lt;/em&gt;, or 557B &lt;em&gt;Do not Wait Houses - Move&lt;/em&gt;, depending on which letter addition was available next. Ehere are, however, exeptions, as for example all lithographs produced with Mourlot.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;edn1&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;_edn1&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;[1]&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;Koschatzky, Walter: &lt;em&gt;Friedensreich Hundertwasser. &lt;/em&gt;The complete graphic work 1951-1986, New York: Rizzoli International Publications, 1986&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;2&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser mastered and innovated many graphic techniques, among them lithograph, silk screen, etching, colour woodcut and many others. He was one of the first to demand and practice complete transparency in terms of technique, dates of creation and editions for each sheet.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser never really created large editions of one and the same graphic work. His graphic editions comprise several colour versions and variants, which are not numbered separately, but instead numbered throughout the entire edition. It was his aim to make many different unique pieces within the art of the graphic, thereby going beyond machine production.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser always took great care to provide exact information about the work on each graphic sheet, in order to arrive at as complete a disclosure of a work&rsquo;s techniques and creation dates as possible.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;On the graphics can be found:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&rsquo;s signature (in manuscript or as Japanese inkan stamps),&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;date and place of the signature,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&oelig;uvre number,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;in many cases the name of the work,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;specimen number,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;listings or stamps and embossings of publishers, printers, paper and paint producers, or of the co-ordinators involved, and&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;colour-separation marks.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Many prints bear embossed, stamped or printed listings of colour variants, technical versions and edition sizes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;On the plates, on the stones or on the screens, additional signatures were often given, but also work numbers, and names, sometimes including the name of the originals, as well as place and date of creation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the case of many Japanese colour woodcuts the title of the work was printed in Japanese characters.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Occasionally Hundertwasser had the reverse of the graphic imprinted with all this information, and even went beyond that by listing the entire development and creative process of the print.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser beherrschte und erneuerte viele graphische Techniken: Lithographie, Siebdruck, Radierung, Farbholzschnitt und andere mehr. Er war einer der ersten, der eine v&ouml;llige Transparenz der Technik, der Entstehungsdaten und Auflage f&uuml;r jedes einzelne Blatt gefordert und eingehalten hat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser hat nie wirklich hohe Auflagen von ein- und derselben Graphik geschaffen. Seine Graphikauflagen bestehen aus mehreren Farbversionen und Varianten, die nicht separat numeriert sind, sondern durch die gesamte Auflage durchnumeriert wurden. Sein Ziel war es, lauter Unikate in der Kunst der Graphik herzustellen und damit die Maschine zu &uuml;berlisten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser war stets darauf bedacht, auf den graphischen Bl&auml;ttern selbst genaue Werkangaben zu machen, um zu einer m&ouml;glichst l&uuml;ckenlosen Offenlegung der Techniken und Entstehungsdaten des Werkes zu gelangen. Auf den Graphiken finden sich:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; Hundertwassers Signatur (handschriftlich und in Form von japanischen Inkans)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; Datum und Ort der Signatur&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; &OElig;uvre-Nummer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; in vielen F&auml;llen der Name des Werkes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; Exemplarnummer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; Nennungen bzw. Stempel und Pr&auml;gungen von Verlegern, Druckern, Papier- und Farbenfabrikanten oder der eingesetzten Koordinatoren&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; Farbauszugspunkte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; Auf vielen Graphiken finden sich gepr&auml;gt, gestempelt oder mitgedruckt Auflistungen von Farbvarianten, technischen Versionen und Auflagenangaben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; In der Platte, im Stein oder im Sieb wurden h&auml;ufig eine zus&auml;tzliche Signatur, aber auch Werknummer und Name, manchmal auch der Name der Vorlage, Entstehungsort und -datum notiert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; In vielen japanischen Farbholzschnitten ist der Titel des Werkes in japanischen Schriftzeichen mitgedruckt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;Mitunter lie&szlig; Hundertwasser die R&uuml;ckseite einer Graphik mit all diesen Informationen bedrucken, ging noch dar&uuml;ber hinaus und hielt dort den gesamten Entwicklungs- und Entstehungsproze&szlig; der Graphik fest. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser hat am Bildrand der Graphiken mit runden Punkten die Arbeit der Techniker und Drucker und somit das vom Ausgangswerk &Uuml;bernommene dokumentiert; quadratische oder numerierte Punkte bezeichnen Hundertwassers eigenh&auml;ndige Arbeit f&uuml;r die Graphik, das f&uuml;r das Werk Neu-Entwickelte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;Walter Koschatzky hat in dem von ihm 1986 herausgegebenen Katalog des graphischen Werkes die Graphiken chronologisch nach dem Erscheinungsdatum gereiht und fortlaufende HWG-Nummern (Hundertwasser-Graphik-Nummern) eingef&uuml;hrt.&lt;a name=&quot;_ednref1&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoEndnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;!--[if !supportFootnotes]--&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoEndnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;[i]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;Mit der Fortsetzung des graphischen Werkes nach 1986 kommt Hundertwassers graphisches Werk auf 124 HWG-Nummern, wobei die 23 Doodles-Radierungen unter einer Nummer, n&auml;mlich&nbsp; 124&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; zusammengefa&szlig;t sind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;Portfolios haben als solche keine eigene HWG-Nummer erhalten, da jede darin befindliche Graphik mit einer HWG-Nummer versehen wurde.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;Wie Walter Koschatzky in seiner Einf&uuml;hrung dargelegt hat, hat Hundertwasser mit Hilfe der &OElig;uvre-Nummer grunds&auml;tzlich verschiedene Arten seiner Graphik gekennzeichnet:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; Werke, die direkt von ihm auf Stein oder auf die Platte gearbeitet, also g&auml;nzlich oder &uuml;berwiegend f&uuml;r diese Ausf&uuml;hrung geschaffen wurden und daher mit einer entsprechenden &OElig;uvre-Nummer versehen sind, zum Beispiel&nbsp; 940&nbsp; &lt;em&gt;&nbsp;Bottlehousebath&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; Werke, die nach einem bestehenden Gem&auml;lde oder Aquarell in ein graphisches Verfahren umgesetzt sind, dabei von ihm selbst auf Platten oder Folien &uuml;berarbeitet wurden und daher nennenswerte Ver&auml;nderungen gegen&uuml;ber der Vorlage aufweisen; auch diese erhielten eine eigene &OElig;uvre-Nummer, beispielsweise 669 &lt;em&gt;King Kong&lt;/em&gt;, nach 202&lt;em&gt; Kopf in zwei Perspektiven&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial&quot;&gt;&ndash; Werke, die von einem bestehenden Gem&auml;lde, Aquarell oder einer Zeichnung in ein Verfahren der Graphik &uuml;bertragen wurden, allerdings vom K&uuml;nstler selbst korrigiert, in Einzelheiten ver&auml;ndert sowie in farbige Varianten gebracht wurden. Ihre Nummern sind diejenigen der Vorlage, sie erhalten aber die Beif&uuml;gung &bdquo;A&ldquo;, &bdquo;B&ldquo; oder &bdquo;C&ldquo;, zum Beispiel&nbsp;&nbsp; 484A&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;em&gt;H&auml;user im Blutregen&lt;/em&gt; oder&nbsp; 557B&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;em&gt;Do not wait Houses &ndash; Move&lt;/em&gt;, je nachdem, welcher Buchstaben-Zusatz der als n&auml;chste frei zu vergeben war. Es gibt aber auch Ausnahmen davon, z. B. alle bei Mourlot entstandenen Lithographien.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;!--[if !supportEndnotes]--&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;!--[endif]--&gt; &lt;div id=&quot;edn1&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoBodyText&quot;&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;_edn1&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoEndnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;!--[if !supportFootnotes]--&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoEndnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;[i]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt&quot;&gt;Koschatzky, Walter: Friedensreich Hundertwasser. Das vollst&auml;ndige druckgraphische Werk 1951&ndash;1986. Fribourg: Office du Livre, Zurich/Schw&auml;bisch Hall: Orell F&uuml;ssli Verlag, 1986&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoEndnoteText&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'',
text_author-'',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;from:&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, p. 60&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;',
text_source_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 51f.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

