%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.3.2.2
object(text,'1.3.2.2','LOS VON LOOS (“LOOSE FROM LOOS”)
A LAW PERMITTING INDIVIDUAL BUILDING ALTERATIONS
OR
ARCHITECTURE-BOYCOTT MANIFESTO
',[
id-105,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-105,
txt-'1.3.2.2',
text_type-6,
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'LOS VON LOOS (&ldquo;LOOSE FROM LOOS&rdquo;)
A LAW PERMITTING INDIVIDUAL BUILDING ALTERATIONS
OR
ARCHITECTURE-BOYCOTT MANIFESTO
',
text_title_ge-'',
text_keywords-'',
text_date-'1968-02-09',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Dear friends,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;People ask me why, as a painter, I meddle in matters of architecture. But as a painter I am also just a man.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Before you sit down anywhere, you first wipe the chair if it is dirty. So if I go into dirty architecture, I must clean that first, too.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;And the dirtier the architecture, the more strongly and effectively its dirt must be combatted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;And this, just this, I did a fortnight ago.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I only enter a house as a free man.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Not as a slave.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Only then can I do anything else, such as painting or saying something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;There is another, very important reason why I choose &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vienna&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; to attack this evil box-prison mischief, namely because I am Austrian, which gives me a moral obligation to do so.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;For it was from &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Austria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; that this architectural crime was launched into the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It is thus from &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Austria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; that reparations must come.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The Austrian Adolf Loos brought this atrocity into the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In 1908, with his manifesto aptly entitled &ldquo;Ornament and Crime&rdquo;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;No doubt he meant well.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Adolf Hitler meant well, too.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;But Adolf Loos was incapable of thinking fifty years ahead.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The world will never be rid of the evil he invoked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It is the duty of myself and all of us to be the first to recognise and combat the catastrophe unleashed in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Austria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; sixty years ago.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Exactly fifty years later, in 1958 in Seckau, I read my &ldquo;Mould Manifesto Against Rationalism in Architecture&rdquo;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I am now no longer alone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;There are architects who have taken it to heart. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Germany&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; holds conference upon conference of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;architects with a conscience, for whom the responsibility for what they are doing is a fearful burden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;But they know no solution.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I have nevertheless seen some new buildings which were not produced on the drawing board.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;That&rsquo;s good. But it is far from being enough.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Back to Loos. Of course it is true that stencilled ornaments were lies. But they were not crimes. Nor did the removal of ornament make houses any more honest. Loos should have replaced sterile ornaments with living growth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;But he did not. He valued the straight line, the identical, the smooth. Now we have the smooth. Everything slips off smoothness. Even God falls down. FOR THE STRAIGHT LINE IS GODLESS. The straight line is the only uncreative line. The only line which does not correspond to man as the image of God.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The straight line is a true tool of the devil. Whosoever uses it is aiding the downfall of mankind. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&ldquo;La ligne droite conduit &agrave; la perte de l&rsquo;humanit&eacute;.&rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;What will this downfall be like? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;We have already had a preliminary taste of it: ten to twenty psychiatrists in every apartment block in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;New York&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Overflowing clinics, where the insane cannot get well because the clinics are also built in the style of Loos.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The diseases of people confined in sterile residential complexes flourish in the deadly monotony. Rashes, ulcers, cancers and strange manners of death all occur. Recovery in such buildings is impossible. Despite psychiatry and health insurance. There are increasing numbers of suicides in the satellite towns, and countless suicide attempts. These are women who cannot get out during the day like the men. We could spend hours listing the miseries which began with Loos. The nihilism of the interned expresses itself through a decline in the desire to work, a decline in production, as psychiatrists and statisticians can surely confirm. For unhappiness, too, can be quantified in figures and money. And thus the damage caused by rational building methods exceeds several times over any apparent savings made. This supplies the proof that rational buildings turn criminal when left as they are. I am not against serial production as such. For the present, unfortunately, we still need it. But to leave serially produced products in the state in which they reach us is an indication of personal bondage, proof that we are slaves.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Help annul the criminal laws suppressing creative building freedom! People do not yet even know they have a right to design their own clothing, their own housing, both inside and out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;A single architect or building sponsor cannot take responsibility for entire apartment blocks, nor even for a single house in which several families are to live. This responsibility must be conceded to each individual resident, whether he be an architect or not.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;All restrictions imposed by building-inspection authorities, leases etc., which forbid or place restraints on individual home improvements, must be lifted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Indeed, it is the duty of the state to provide financial assistance and support to every citizen wishing to undertake individual alterations, whether to outside walls or indoors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Man has a particular claim to his architectural outer skin. With one condition: neither the neighbours of those implementing modifications nor the stability of the house may suffer as a result. But that is why we have technical experts who can calculate everything so nicely.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Tenants as well as owners must have the option of exercising their window right, that is, of making home improvements inside and out. Only where the subsequent tenant does not accept such alterations should the apartment be returned to its original state. But it can assumed with 90% certainty that individual improvements will be highly welcome to the next tenant, since their aim will have been to make an apartment more humane.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;If such a law on individual building alterations is not passed, the prison psychosis of interned residents will continue to worsen until it reaches a terrible end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;There are only two options: either absolute slavery or rebellion against the restrictions of personal freedom.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;If the law on individual building alterations is not passed, I demand countermeasures to go into effect immediately.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;There are several possibilities:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 18pt; text-indent: -18pt&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;1. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Boycott. People should refuse to use these slave cages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 18pt&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;They should refuse to enter them. If a person is invited to go somewhere, be it to friends or the police, and the building is a sterile box, he or she should go to the next public telephone and ask the person to come out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 18pt&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 18pt; text-indent: -18pt&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;2. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Architectural change through the visitor. I demonstrated this for the first time personally in a student dormitory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Only enter a slave cage if you can change it architecturally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;By pouring black and red paint on the sterile wall and taking off all my clothes and giving my speech in the nude, I acquired the moral right to be present in this sterile cage at all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Now, there are unconscious architectural revolts and changes already; and many kinds of unconscious boycotts, as well: there are shootings and street riots such as those in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Chicago&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. There are bombings in wartime. There is increasing juvenile delinquency in the new neighbourhoods of cities. There is the rowdyism of drunks. There is the escapism of leather jackets and hippies. There is the escape to one&rsquo;s annual holiday and the bitter homecoming. There is the escape to the cinema, television, books. There is the escape to art, music. There is the escape to the world of dreams, alcohol and drugs. There is the escape to death.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Whose fault is this? The cowardly architects, the jumping jacks of their unscrupulous clients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In any case: those who flee, rebel or commit suicide are well off. But those who do not have these escape options lose their soul, their humanity, their most sacred asset and everything else besides.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;No, I propose: do not destroy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;do not rebel&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;do not flee&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;just change&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;and everything will be all right.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I&rsquo;ll tell you now how I can conceive this. I will carry a kilogramme of plaster of paris around with me. If I receive an invitation to go somewhere, I will have a look at the building first. If it is a smooth one in which people are confined who are not allowed to do anything, who can do nothing, want to do nothing, I will insist on putting a nice hump of plaster of paris on the wall with my own hands. If I am not permitted to do this, I won&rsquo;t go in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I call on you to do this or similar things if you have a conscience. For if you eat out of the hand of this sterile architecture, it arouses the suspicion that you like the taste.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;If, for example, 100 individual mounds of plaster of paris were put on a sterile District Administration building every day, even this building would soon be better and prettier.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Or the tenants in a building in which all the flats, the ones adjacent, above, below, are the same refuse to pay the rent as long as they are not permitted to make building alterations with their own hands.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Or: workers refuse to walk or ride through a street where sterile fa&ccedil;ades are to the right and left.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Just as every deer refuses to go where it has qualms about doing so.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Or: a piece of iron can be used to scrape things in the smooth outer skin, as is done in public toilets. Look at the dreadful enslavement we are in that the last remnants of individual creativity can only be found in toilets. The last place of freedom.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The only free buildings we still have are the &lt;em&gt;Schreberg&auml;rten&lt;/em&gt; (huts in the workers&rsquo; allotment garden plots).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Every architect has the sacred duty to say that what he has erected here is by far not all. That it is only a miserable skeleton that the occupants have to remodel; that he is himself incapable of building a home for eve&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;ryo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;ne. His duty is solely to make the skeleton strong and variable enough so that partial architectural changes can be carried out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Since in cities eve&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;ryo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;ne no longer finds quarters on the ground floor, he, the builder, has to create planes superimposed above one another. But with that his mission is already at an end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The portion of the earth which is covered over and killed by the building construction must be transferred to the roof. A layer of earth so thick that huge, 100-year-old trees can grow on the roof. It is incomprehensible why the roofs of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vienna&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; are not being used as parks and forests.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;People will say: such trees on the roofs cost more than the house itself.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;But I am sure that in a few years they will be forced to issue a building ordinance requiring every house, every garage, every factory, particularly every factory, to have a layer of earth on the roof one metre deep. For meadows, forests, parks, gardens and agriculture with cows.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;And that won&rsquo;t be enough. They will be forced to add on four storeys of forest and meadows for every storey of human dwellings. So a ten-storey building will have to superimpose eight layers of forest over only two layers of people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Now I have a suggestion to make: Ernst Fuchs, Arnulf Rainer and I make up the Pintorarium, a free association of fundamentally different, not yet corrupted energies. How about having each of us, Arnulf Rainer, Ernst Fuchs and I, being assigned one existing and inhabited sterile building for remodelling? (In the meantime, following my example, the painters Brauer, Kumpf, Fuchs, Oberhuber and Attersee have built houses or been involved in architectural activities; addendum by Hundertwasser, 1996.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vienna&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; the wrappings and shells are so important that people think they can do without the core. Woe to him who takes away the wrappings. Our cowardice, our lie is huge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I am in the process of liberating myself of it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I have tried to concentrate nakedly on the truth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It is very hard.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;You are vulnerable to everything if you have nothing on. But the victory is great.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It is a good feeling.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It would be good if our government would also muster the courage to speak to the public in the nude. It makes you feel good when you do your duty. I feel very good.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Dear friends,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;People ask me why, as a painter, I meddle in matters of architecture. But as a painter I am also just a man.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Before you sit down anywhere, you first wipe the chair if it is dirty. So if I go into dirty architecture, I must clean that first, too.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;And the dirtier the architecture, the more strongly and effectively its dirt must be combatted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;And this, just this, I did a fortnight ago.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I only enter a house as a free man.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Not as a slave.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Only then can I do anything else, such as painting or saying something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;There is another, very important reason why I choose &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vienna&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; to attack this evil box-prison mischief, namely because I am Austrian, which gives me a moral obligation to do so.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;For it was from &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Austria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; that this architectural crime was launched into the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It is thus from &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Austria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; that reparations must come.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The Austrian Adolf Loos brought this atrocity into the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In 1908, with his manifesto aptly entitled &ldquo;Ornament and Crime&rdquo;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;No doubt he meant well.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Adolf Hitler meant well, too.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;But Adolf Loos was incapable of thinking fifty years ahead.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The world will never be rid of the evil he invoked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It is the duty of myself and all of us to be the first to recognise and combat the catastrophe unleashed in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Austria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; sixty years ago.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Exactly fifty years later, in 1958 in Seckau, I read my &ldquo;Mould Manifesto Against Rationalism in Architecture&rdquo;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I am now no longer alone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;There are architects who have taken it to heart. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Germany&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; holds conference upon conference of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;architects with a conscience, for whom the responsibility for what they are doing is a fearful burden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;But they know no solution.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I have nevertheless seen some new buildings which were not produced on the drawing board.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;That&rsquo;s good. But it is far from being enough.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Back to Loos. Of course it is true that stencilled ornaments were lies. But they were not crimes. Nor did the removal of ornament make houses any more honest. Loos should have replaced sterile ornaments with living growth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;But he did not. He valued the straight line, the identical, the smooth. Now we have the smooth. Everything slips off smoothness. Even God falls down. FOR THE STRAIGHT LINE IS GODLESS. The straight line is the only uncreative line. The only line which does not correspond to man as the image of God.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The straight line is a true tool of the devil. Whosoever uses it is aiding the downfall of mankind. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&ldquo;La ligne droite conduit &agrave; la perte de l&rsquo;humanit&eacute;.&rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;What will this downfall be like? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;We have already had a preliminary taste of it: ten to twenty psychiatrists in every apartment block in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;New York&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Overflowing clinics, where the insane cannot get well because the clinics are also built in the style of Loos.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The diseases of people confined in sterile residential complexes flourish in the deadly monotony. Rashes, ulcers, cancers and strange manners of death all occur. Recovery in such buildings is impossible. Despite psychiatry and health insurance. There are increasing numbers of suicides in the satellite towns, and countless suicide attempts. These are women who cannot get out during the day like the men. We could spend hours listing the miseries which began with Loos. The nihilism of the interned expresses itself through a decline in the desire to work, a decline in production, as psychiatrists and statisticians can surely confirm. For unhappiness, too, can be quantified in figures and money. And thus the damage caused by rational building methods exceeds several times over any apparent savings made. This supplies the proof that rational buildings turn criminal when left as they are. I am not against serial production as such. For the present, unfortunately, we still need it. But to leave serially produced products in the state in which they reach us is an indication of personal bondage, proof that we are slaves.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Help annul the criminal laws suppressing creative building freedom! People do not yet even know they have a right to design their own clothing, their own housing, both inside and out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;A single architect or building sponsor cannot take responsibility for entire apartment blocks, nor even for a single house in which several families are to live. This responsibility must be conceded to each individual resident, whether he be an architect or not.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;All restrictions imposed by building-inspection authorities, leases etc., which forbid or place restraints on individual home improvements, must be lifted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Indeed, it is the duty of the state to provide financial assistance and support to every citizen wishing to undertake individual alterations, whether to outside walls or indoors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Man has a particular claim to his architectural outer skin. With one condition: neither the neighbours of those implementing modifications nor the stability of the house may suffer as a result. But that is why we have technical experts who can calculate everything so nicely.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Tenants as well as owners must have the option of exercising their window right, that is, of making home improvements inside and out. Only where the subsequent tenant does not accept such alterations should the apartment be returned to its original state. But it can assumed with 90% certainty that individual improvements will be highly welcome to the next tenant, since their aim will have been to make an apartment more humane.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;If such a law on individual building alterations is not passed, the prison psychosis of interned residents will continue to worsen until it reaches a terrible end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;There are only two options: either absolute slavery or rebellion against the restrictions of personal freedom.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;If the law on individual building alterations is not passed, I demand countermeasures to go into effect immediately.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;There are several possibilities:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 18pt; text-indent: -18pt&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;1. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Boycott. People should refuse to use these slave cages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 18pt&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;They should refuse to enter them. If a person is invited to go somewhere, be it to friends or the police, and the building is a sterile box, he or she should go to the next public telephone and ask the person to come out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 18pt&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 18pt; text-indent: -18pt&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;2. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Architectural change through the visitor. I demonstrated this for the first time personally in a student dormitory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Only enter a slave cage if you can change it architecturally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;By pouring black and red paint on the sterile wall and taking off all my clothes and giving my speech in the nude, I acquired the moral right to be present in this sterile cage at all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Now, there are unconscious architectural revolts and changes already; and many kinds of unconscious boycotts, as well: there are shootings and street riots such as those in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Chicago&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. There are bombings in wartime. There is increasing juvenile delinquency in the new neighbourhoods of cities. There is the rowdyism of drunks. There is the escapism of leather jackets and hippies. There is the escape to one&rsquo;s annual holiday and the bitter homecoming. There is the escape to the cinema, television, books. There is the escape to art, music. There is the escape to the world of dreams, alcohol and drugs. There is the escape to death.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Whose fault is this? The cowardly architects, the jumping jacks of their unscrupulous clients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In any case: those who flee, rebel or commit suicide are well off. But those who do not have these escape options lose their soul, their humanity, their most sacred asset and everything else besides.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;No, I propose: do not destroy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;do not rebel&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;do not flee&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;just change&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;and everything will be all right.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I&rsquo;ll tell you now how I can conceive this. I will carry a kilogramme of plaster of paris around with me. If I receive an invitation to go somewhere, I will have a look at the building first. If it is a smooth one in which people are confined who are not allowed to do anything, who can do nothing, want to do nothing, I will insist on putting a nice hump of plaster of paris on the wall with my own hands. If I am not permitted to do this, I won&rsquo;t go in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I call on you to do this or similar things if you have a conscience. For if you eat out of the hand of this sterile architecture, it arouses the suspicion that you like the taste.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;If, for example, 100 individual mounds of plaster of paris were put on a sterile District Administration building every day, even this building would soon be better and prettier.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Or the tenants in a building in which all the flats, the ones adjacent, above, below, are the same refuse to pay the rent as long as they are not permitted to make building alterations with their own hands.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Or: workers refuse to walk or ride through a street where sterile fa&ccedil;ades are to the right and left.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Just as every deer refuses to go where it has qualms about doing so.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Or: a piece of iron can be used to scrape things in the smooth outer skin, as is done in public toilets. Look at the dreadful enslavement we are in that the last remnants of individual creativity can only be found in toilets. The last place of freedom.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The only free buildings we still have are the &lt;em&gt;Schreberg&auml;rten&lt;/em&gt; (huts in the workers&rsquo; allotment garden plots).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Every architect has the sacred duty to say that what he has erected here is by far not all. That it is only a miserable skeleton that the occupants have to remodel; that he is himself incapable of building a home for eve&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;ryo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;ne. His duty is solely to make the skeleton strong and variable enough so that partial architectural changes can be carried out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Since in cities eve&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;ryo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;ne no longer finds quarters on the ground floor, he, the builder, has to create planes superimposed above one another. But with that his mission is already at an end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;The portion of the earth which is covered over and killed by the building construction must be transferred to the roof. A layer of earth so thick that huge, 100-year-old trees can grow on the roof. It is incomprehensible why the roofs of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vienna&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; are not being used as parks and forests.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;People will say: such trees on the roofs cost more than the house itself.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;But I am sure that in a few years they will be forced to issue a building ordinance requiring every house, every garage, every factory, particularly every factory, to have a layer of earth on the roof one metre deep. For meadows, forests, parks, gardens and agriculture with cows.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;And that won&rsquo;t be enough. They will be forced to add on four storeys of forest and meadows for every storey of human dwellings. So a ten-storey building will have to superimpose eight layers of forest over only two layers of people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Now I have a suggestion to make: Ernst Fuchs, Arnulf Rainer and I make up the Pintorarium, a free association of fundamentally different, not yet corrupted energies. How about having each of us, Arnulf Rainer, Ernst Fuchs and I, being assigned one existing and inhabited sterile building for remodelling? (In the meantime, following my example, the painters Brauer, Kumpf, Fuchs, Oberhuber and Attersee have built houses or been involved in architectural activities; addendum by Hundertwasser, 1996.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vienna&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; the wrappings and shells are so important that people think they can do without the core. Woe to him who takes away the wrappings. Our cowardice, our lie is huge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I am in the process of liberating myself of it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;I have tried to concentrate nakedly on the truth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It is very hard.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;You are vulnerable to everything if you have nothing on. But the victory is great.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It is a good feeling.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;It would be good if our government would also muster the courage to speak to the public in the nude. It makes you feel good when you do your duty. I feel very good.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Liebe Leute,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;man fragt mich, wieso ich mich als Maler &uuml;berhaupt in die Angelegenheiten der Architektur einmische. Nun, als Maler bin ich auch nur ein Mensch. Und wenn man sich irgendwo hinsetzt, dann wischt man auch erst den Stuhl ab, wenn er schmutzig ist. Also: wenn ich in eine schmutzige Architektur hineingehe, so mu&szlig; ich sie auch erst entschmutzen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Und je schmutziger die Architektur, desto st&auml;rker und wirksamer mu&szlig; die Bek&auml;mpfung des Schmutzes sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Ich gehe als freier Mensch in ein Haus hinein. Nicht als Sklave. Erst dann kann ich alles weitere tun, wie zum Beispiel malen oder etwas sagen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Einen anderen, sehr wichtigen Grund habe ich, diesen Schachtelgef&auml;ngnis-Unfug gerade in Wien anzugreifen. Und zwar als &Ouml;sterreicher. Und da habe ich sogar eine moralische Verpflichtung. Denn von &Ouml;sterreich aus ging dieses Architektur-Verbrechen in die Welt. Daher mu&szlig; von hier aus die Wiedergutmachung einsetzen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Der &Ouml;sterreicher Adolf Loos hat diese Schandtat in die Welt gesetzt, bereits 1908 und sinnigerweise mit seinem Manifest &bdquo;Ornament und Verbrechen&ldquo;. Sicher hat er es gut gemeint. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Auch Adolf Hitler hat es gut gemeint. Aber Adolf Loos war unf&auml;hig, f&uuml;nfzig Jahre vorauszudenken. Der Teufel, den er rief, den wird die Welt nun nicht mehr los.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Es ist meine und unser aller Pflicht, das Verh&auml;ngnis, das vor sechzig Jahren von &Ouml;sterreich aus seinen Lauf nahm, hier, gerade hier, als erste zu erkennen und zu bek&auml;mpfen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Genau f&uuml;nfzig Jahre danach, 1958 in Seckau, habe ich mein &bdquo;Verschimmelungsmanifest gegen den Rationalismus in der Architektur&ldquo; verlesen. Jetzt bin ich nicht mehr alleine. Es gibt Architekten, die es sich zu Herzen nehmen. In Deutschland findet eine Tagung nach der anderen statt von Architekten mit Gewissen, die die Verantwortung f&uuml;r das, was sie tun, ganz entsetzlich dr&uuml;ckt. Aber sie wissen keinen Ausweg. Und doch habe ich bereits neue Geb&auml;ude gesehen, die nicht am Rei&szlig;brett entstanden sind. Das tut gut. Aber das ist alles noch zu wenig.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Zur&uuml;ck zu Loos. Nat&uuml;rlich stimmt es, da&szlig; die schablonierten Ornamente L&uuml;ge waren. Verbrechen waren sie nicht. Durch die Abnahme der Ornamente wurden aber die H&auml;user nicht ehrlicher. Loos h&auml;tte das sterile Ornament durch lebendes Wachstum ersetzen sollen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Das tat er nicht. Er pries die gerade Linie, das Gleiche und das Glatte. Jetzt haben wir das Glatte. Auf dem Glatten rutscht alles aus. Auch der liebe Gott f&auml;llt hin. Denn die gerade Linie ist gottlos. Die gerade Linie ist die einzige unsch&ouml;pferische Linie. Die einzige Linie, die dem Menschen als Ebenbild Gottes nicht entspricht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Die gerade Linie ist ein wahres Werkzeug des Teufels. Wer sich ihrer bedient, hilft mit am Untergang der Menschheit. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;La ligne droite conduit &agrave; la perte de l&rsquo;humanit&eacute;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Wie wird der Untergang sein? Einen Vorgeschmack haben wir schon: In jedem Wohnblock in New York zehn bis zwanzig Psychiater. Die Kliniken &uuml;berf&uuml;llt, wo die Irren nicht gesund werden k&ouml;nnen, weil die Kliniken auch nach Loos gebaut worden sind. Die Krankheiten der Menschen, die in den sterilen Reihenh&auml;usern interniert sind, gedeihen in der t&ouml;dlichen Eint&ouml;nigkeit. Es kommen Ausschl&auml;ge, Geschw&uuml;re, Krebs und seltsame Todesarten. Genesung ist in diesen Geb&auml;uden unm&ouml;glich. Trotz Psychiatrie und Krankenkasse. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In den Satellitenst&auml;dten z&auml;hlt man mehr und mehr Selbstmorde. Und unz&auml;hlige Selbstmordversuche. Es sind Frauen, die nicht wie die M&auml;nner tags&uuml;ber weggehen k&ouml;nnen. Stundenlang kann man &uuml;ber das Elend berichten, das mit Loos begann.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Der Nihilismus der Internierten dr&uuml;ckt sich in einer Abnahme der Arbeitslust, in einer Abnahme der Produktion aus. Das k&ouml;nnen mir Psychiater und Statistiker sicher best&auml;tigen. Denn auch das Ungl&uuml;cklichsein kann man in Zahlen und in Geld ausdr&uuml;cken. Und so ist der Schaden, den die rationelle Bauweise anrichtet, um ein Vielfaches h&ouml;her als die scheinbare Einsparung. Und somit ist der Beweis erbracht, da&szlig; die rationellen Bauten kriminell werden, wenn man sie in diesem Zustand bel&auml;&szlig;t. Ich bin nicht so sehr gegen die Serienherstellung. Die braucht man leider vorl&auml;ufig noch. Aber in Serien hergestellte Dinge so zu belassen, wie man sie bekommt, ist ein Beweis f&uuml;r die eigene Unfreiheit, ein Beweis daf&uuml;r, da&szlig; man Sklave ist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Helft mit, die verbrecherischen Gesetze zur Unterdr&uuml;ckung der sch&ouml;pferischen Bau-Freiheit zu annullieren! Die Leute wissen ja noch gar nicht, da&szlig; es ihr Recht ist, ihre Kleidung innen und au&szlig;en, ihre Behausung innen und au&szlig;en selbst zu gestalten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Ein einziger Architekt oder Bauherr kann nicht die Verantwortung f&uuml;r ganze Wohnblocks tragen, ja nicht einmal mehr f&uuml;r ein einziges Haus, in dem mehrere Familien wohnen. Diese Verantwortung mu&szlig; jedem einzelnen Bewohner zugestanden werden, ob er nun Architekt ist oder nicht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Alle Verbote der Baupolizei, der Mietvertr&auml;ge und so weiter, die individuelle Ver&auml;nderungen am Haus unm&ouml;glich machen oder einschr&auml;nken, m&uuml;ssen aufgehoben werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Ja, es ist sogar die Pflicht des Staates, jedem B&uuml;rger, der individuelle Ver&auml;nderungen vornehmen will, sei es an der Au&szlig;enmauer oder innen, finanziell zu unterst&uuml;tzen und beizustehen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Der Mensch hat insbesondere ein Anrecht auf seine architektonische Au&szlig;enhaut. Eine einzige Bedingung: Die Nachbarn des Ver&auml;nderers und die Stabilit&auml;t des Hauses d&uuml;rfen nicht leiden. Aber dazu sind ja die Techniker da, die alles so sch&ouml;n berechnen k&ouml;nnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Nicht nur der Wohnungseigent&uuml;mer, auch der Mieter mu&szlig; die M&ouml;glichkeit haben, alles architektonisch zu ver&auml;ndern. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Nur wenn der nach ihm einziehende Mieter mit den baulichen Ver&auml;nderungen nicht einverstanden ist, soll der vorherige Zustand wiederhergestellt werden. Es ist jedoch mit 90prozentiger Sicherheit anzunehmen, da&szlig; die individuellen architektonischen Verbesserungen, die sowieso zum Menschlichen hin tendieren, dem nachfolgenden Mieter h&ouml;chst willkommen sein werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Wenn dieses Individuelle-Bauver&auml;nderungs-Gesetz nicht herauskommt, wird sich die Gef&auml;ngnis-Psychose der Internierten bis zu einem entsetzlichen Ende verst&auml;rken. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Es gibt nur zwei M&ouml;glichkeiten: entweder absolute Versklavung oder Auflehnung gegen die Verbote der individuellen Freiheit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Falls das Individuelle-Bauver&auml;nderungs-Gesetz nicht herauskommt, fordere ich ab sofort Gegenma&szlig;nahmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Es gibt da mehrere M&ouml;glichkeiten:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;1. Der Boykott. Man weigere sich, diese Sklavenk&auml;fige zu ben&uuml;tzen. Man weigere sich, hineinzugehen. Wenn man irgendwohin eingeladen ist, sei es zu Freunden oder zur Polizei, und das Haus ist eine sterile Schachtel, so gehe man zum n&auml;chsten Telefon und bitte die Person heraus.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;2. Die architektonische Ver&auml;nderung durch den Besucher. Ich habe dies &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;pers&ouml;nlich zum ersten Mal in einem Studentenheim demonstriert. Man gehe in einen Sklavenk&auml;fig nur dann hinein, wenn man ihn architektonisch ver&auml;ndern kann. Dadurch, da&szlig; ich schwarze und rote Farbe an die sterile Wand go&szlig; und mich nackt auszog und nur im nackten Zustand meine Ansprache hielt, hatte ich mir das moralische Recht erworben, in diesem sterilen K&auml;fig &uuml;berhaupt anwesend zu sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Nun gibt es sowieso schon unbewu&szlig;te architektonische Revolten und Ver&auml;nderungen. Und auch viele Arten von unbewu&szlig;tem Boykott: Da sind die Schie&szlig;ereien und Stra&szlig;enschlachten wie in Chicago. Da sind die Bombenw&uuml;rfe im Krieg. Da ist die zunehmende Jugendkriminalit&auml;t in den neuen Stadtvierteln. Da ist das Randalieren der Besoffenen. Da ist der Ausbruch der Lederjacken und der Hippies. Da ist die Flucht in den Urlaub und die bittere R&uuml;ckkehr. Da ist die Flucht ins Kino, in die Television, in die B&uuml;cher. Da ist die Flucht in die Kunst, in die Musik. Da ist die Flucht in die Welt der Tr&auml;ume, des Alkohols und des Rauschgiftes. Da ist die Flucht in den Tod. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Wer ist schuld daran? Die feigen Architekten, Hampelm&auml;nner ihrer skrupellosen Auftraggeber.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Jedenfalls: Die, die fliehen, revoltieren oder Selbstmord begehen, haben es noch gut. Aber die, die diese Ausweichm&ouml;glichkeiten nicht haben, verlieren ihre Seele, ihr Menschtum, ihr heiligstes Gut und alles andere sowieso. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Ich aber schlage vor:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Nicht zu revoltieren, nicht zu fliehen, nur zu &auml;ndern und alles wird wieder gut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Ich sage zuerst einmal, wie ich mir das vorstelle. Ich werde ein Kilogramm Gips mit mir herumtragen. Wenn ich irgendwo eingeladen bin, werde ich mir das Haus erst ansehen. Wenn es ein glatter Bau ist, in dem Leute interniert sind, die nichts tun d&uuml;rfen, nichts tun k&ouml;nnen, nichts tun wollen, werde ich darauf bestehen, eine sch&ouml;ne Gipserhebung eigenh&auml;ndig an der Au&szlig;enwand des Hauses anzubringen. Falls ich das nicht tun darf, gehe ich nicht hinein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Ich fordere euch auf, dies oder &auml;hnliches zu tun, wenn ihr ein Gewissen habt. Denn wenn ihr dieser sterilen Architektur aus der Hand fre&szlig;t, entsteht der Verdacht, sie schmeckt euch. Wenn zum Beispiel t&auml;glich 100 individuelle H&uuml;gel Gips an einem sterilen Bezirksamt angebracht werden, so wird selbst dieses Geb&auml;ude rasch besser und sch&ouml;ner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Oder aber die Mieter weigern sich, in einem Haus, in dem ganz gleiche Wohnungen daneben dar&uuml;ber und darunter sind, den Zins zu zahlen, so lange sie nicht eigenh&auml;ndig umbauen d&uuml;rfen. Oder: Werkt&auml;tige weigern sich durch eine Stra&szlig;e zu gehen oder zu fahren, wo rechts und links sterile Hausfassaden sind. So wie sich jedes Reh weigert zu gehen, wo ihm nicht geheuer ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Oder: Man kann mit einem St&uuml;ck Eisen Dinge in die glatten Au&szlig;enmauern ritzen, &auml;hnlich wie man es in den Aborten sowieso tut. Was haben wir f&uuml;r eine sch&auml;ndliche Versklavung, da&szlig; die letzten &Uuml;berbleibsel der individuellen Gestaltung sich nur noch in den Klosetten finden, den letzten Orten der Freiheit. Die einzigen freien Geb&auml;ude, die wir noch haben, sind die Schrebergartenh&auml;user.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Jeder Architekt hat die heilige Pflicht zu sagen, da&szlig; das, was er da hingestellt hat, noch lange nicht alles ist. Da&szlig; es erst ein elendiges Gerippe ist, das die Bewohner erst umgestalten m&uuml;ssen; da&szlig; er selbst unf&auml;hig ist, jedem ein eigenes Heim zu bauen. Seine Pflicht ist nur die eine: das Gerippe stark genug und variabel genug zu machen, so da&szlig; bauliche Teil-Ver&auml;nderungen durchf&uuml;hrbar sind. Da in den St&auml;dten nicht mehr alle zu ebener Erde unterkommen, hat er als Konstrukteur die Ebenen &uuml;bereinander zu schaffen. Damit aber ist seine Mission auch schon zu Ende.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Das Erdst&uuml;ck, das beim Hausbau zugedeckt und umgebracht wird, mu&szlig; auf das Dach verlegt werden. Eine dicke Erdschicht, da&szlig; auf den D&auml;chern hundertj&auml;hrige B&auml;ume, riesige B&auml;ume, wachsen k&ouml;nnen. Es ist unverst&auml;ndlich, wieso die Flachd&auml;cher Wiens nicht als Parkanlagen genutzt werden. Man wird sagen: Solche W&auml;lder auf D&auml;chern kosten mehr als das Haus selbst. Aber ich bin sicher: In wenigen Jahren wird man gezwungen sein, ein Baugesetz herauszubringen, das f&uuml;r jedes Haus, f&uuml;r jede Garage, f&uuml;r jede Fabrik, besonders f&uuml;r jede Fabrik, eine ein bis zwei Meter hohe Erdschicht auf dem Dach vorschreibt. F&uuml;r Wiesen, Wald, Parkanlagen, G&auml;rten und Landwirtschaft mit K&uuml;hen. Und dies wird nicht gen&uuml;gen. Man wird gezwungen sein, zu jedem Stockwerk Menschenbehausung vier Stockwerke Wald und Wiese dazuzubauen. Also ein zehngescho&szlig;iges Geb&auml;ude wird &uuml;bereinander acht Schichten Wald haben m&uuml;ssen f&uuml;r nur zwei Schichten Mensch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Nun h&auml;tte ich einen Vorschlag: Ernst Fuchs, Arnulf Rainer und ich bilden das Pintorarium, eine freie Vereinigung grundverschiedener, noch nicht korrupter Kr&auml;fte. Wie w&auml;re es, wenn jeder von uns, Arnulf Rainer, Ernst Fuchs und ich, je ein bereits bestehendes und bewohntes steriles Haus zur Umgestaltung zugeteilt bek&auml;men? (Inzwischen haben meinem Beispiel folgend die Maler Brauer, Kumpf, Fuchs, Oberhuber und Attersee H&auml;user gebaut bzw. sich architektonisch bet&auml;tigt; Bemerkung von Hundertwasser, 1996)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;In Wien sind die H&uuml;llen und Schalen so wichtig, da&szlig; man glaubt, ohne den Kern auszukommen. Wehe, wenn man die Umh&uuml;llungen wegnimmt. Unsere Feigheit, unsere L&uuml;ge ist riesengro&szlig;. Ich bin dabei, mich davon zu befreien. Ich habe versucht, mich nackt auf die Wahrheit zu konzentrieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Es ist sehr schwer. Man ist allem ausgesetzt, wenn man nichts anhat. Aber der Sieg ist gro&szlig;. Es ist ein gutes Gef&uuml;hl. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Es w&auml;re gut, wenn unsere Regierung auch den Mut aufbringen w&uuml;rde, nackt zur &Ouml;ffentlichkeit zu sprechen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Es tut gut, wenn man seine Pflicht tut. Ich f&uuml;hle mich sehr wohl.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_occasion_en-'Speech in Concordia Hall, Vienna, 9 February 1968 (held in German).',
text_occasion_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vorgetragen am 9. Februar 1968 im Concordiasaal in Wien.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser&rsquo;s private print with manifestos and speeches in the nude in 1967 and 1968. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vienna, 2&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt; edition, 1968 (German)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;protokolle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Zeitschrift&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. edited by Otto Breicha and Gerhard Fritsch. Jugend und Volk: Vienna, 1968, pp. 56-63 (German) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Exhibition catalogue for Haus der Kunst, Munich 1975. Gruener Janura AG: Glarus/Switzerland, 1975, pp. 356-365 (German)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Catalogues of the World Travelling Museum Exhibition 1975&ndash;1987: &lt;u&gt;French edition:&lt;/u&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Paris&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Luxembourg&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, Marseille, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Cairo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1975; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Copenhagen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Dakar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1976; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Montreal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Brussels&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1978. &lt;u&gt;English edition:&lt;/u&gt; Tel Aviv, Reykjavik, 1976; Cape Town, Pretoria, Rio de Janeiro, S&atilde;o Paulo, Brasilia, Caracas, 1977; Mexico City, Toronto, 1978; Rome, H&oslash;vikodden, 1980; Helsinki, 1981; London, 1983. &lt;u&gt;German edition:&lt;/u&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Warsaw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1976; Pf&auml;ffikon/Lake Zurich, 1979; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Cologne&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1980; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Vienna&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Graz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1981. &lt;u&gt;Japanese / English edition: &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Tokyo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1977.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Breicha, Otto; Urbach Reinhard: &Ouml;sterreich zum Beispiel. (Austria for example) Literatur, Bildende Kunst, Film und Musik seit 1968. Residenz Verlag: Salzburg, pp. 68-72 (German)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Deutscher Taschenbuch Verlag (dtv): Munich, 1983, pp. 174-179 and ed. 2004 (Langen M&uuml;ller Verlag, Munich), pp. 227-231 (German)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus (The Hundertwasser House). &Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag/Compress Verlag: Vienna, 1985, pp. 61-64 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;German&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Rand, Harry: Friedensreich Hundertwasser. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Taschen: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Cologne&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1991, pp. 138-139 (excerpt), abridged edition 1993 and edition 2003, pp. 118-119 (excerpt) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser Architecture. For a More Human Architecture in Harmony with Nature. Taschen: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Cologne&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1997, pp. 58-61 (English) and German edition 2006, pp. 44-47&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Hundertwassers Privatdruck &uuml;ber die Manifeste und die Nacktreden 1967 und 1968. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Wien, 2. Auflage, 1968&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Protokolle. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. hrg. von Otto Breicha und Gerhard Fritsch. Jugend und Volk: Wien 1968, S. 56-63&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Katalog zur Ausstellung im Haus der Kunst, M&uuml;nchen 1975. Gruener Janura AG: Glarus/Schweiz 1975, S. 356-365&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Kataloge zur Welt-Wanderausstellung 1975&ndash;1987: &lt;u&gt;Franz&ouml;sische Ausgabe:&lt;/u&gt; Paris, Luxemburg, Marseille, Kairo, 1975; Kopenhagen, Dakar, 1976; Montreal, Br&uuml;ssel, 1978. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Englische Ausgabe:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; Tel Aviv, Reykjavik, 1976; Cape Town, Pretoria, Rio de Janeiro, S&atilde;o Paulo, Brasilia, Caracas, 1977; Mexiko City, Toronto, 1978; Rom, H&oslash;vikodden, 1980; Helsinki, 1981; London, 1983. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Deutsche Ausgabe:&lt;/u&gt; Warschau, 1976; Pf&auml;ffikon (Schweiz), 1979; K&ouml;ln, 1980; Wien, Graz, 1981. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Japanische / Englische Ausgabe:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Tokyo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;, 1977.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Breicha, Otto; Urbach Reinhard: &Ouml;sterreich zum Beispiel. Literatur, Bildende Kunst, Film und Musik seit 1968. Residenz Verlag: Salzburg, S. 68-72&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Deutscher Taschenbuch Verlag (dtv): M&uuml;nchen 1983, S. 174-179 und Ausgabe 2004 (Langen M&uuml;ller Verlag, M&uuml;nchen), S. 227-231&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus. &Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag/Compress Verlag: Wien 1985, S. 61-64&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; color: black&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; color: red; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Rand, Harry: Friedensreich Hundertwasser. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Taschen: K&ouml;ln 1991, S. 138-139 (Auszug), gek&uuml;rzte Ausgabe 1993 und Ausgabe 2003, S. 118-119 (Auszug) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; color: black&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; color: black&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser Architektur. F&uuml;r ein natur- und menschengerechteres Bauen. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 1996, S. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; color: black&quot;&gt;58-61&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; color: black&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; color: black&quot;&gt;&nbsp;und erweiterte Neuausgabe 2006, S. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; color: black&quot;&gt;44-47&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
