%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.3.3.2.1
object(text,'1.3.3.2.1','Speeches in the Nude for the Right to a Third Skin MORE',[
id-116,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-116,
txt-'1.3.3.2.1',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'Speeches in the Nude for the Right to a Third Skin MORE',
text_title_ge-'',
text_keywords-'',
text_date-'2006-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser held his first speech in the nude on 12 December 1967 at the Hartmann Gallery in Munich, during an action of the &lt;em&gt;Pintorarium&lt;/em&gt; and in presence of the other Pintorarium members, the painters Arnulf Rainer and Ernst Fuchs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The wording of the Munich speech was preserved, whereas the second speech in the nude held shortly after at the International Student Dormitory in Vienna was not recorded. However it exists a protocol from 26 January 1968 in which Hundertwasser exposed the circumstances and motifs for his nude demonstration against rationalism in architecture.&nbsp; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser was invited in connection with the exhibition of his works at the International Student Dormitory to be present at the opening and to speak to the students.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;As he assumed that the building was a modern functional construction, he took along two hollow eggs filled with India ink. He wanted to make a drastic and symbolic change in the architecture by applying black and red ink to the lifeless walls. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser played a record by the painter Arik Bauer (&ldquo;Don&rsquo;t Believe in the T-square&rdquo;), then he threw the two eggs. He quickly undressed and made a speech, stating that the architecture in which the dormitory was built should be rejected and appealing to the students to oppose such oppression which forced them to study in rooms similar to prison cells.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser explained his motifs for the speech in the nude as follows:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&bdquo;It is my conviction that man is surrounded by three layers: by his skin, his clothing and a building. Clothing and buildings have undergone a development in the last centuries which is not longer in tune with nature and the requirements of the individual. As a consequence of the mass aspects of society, inappropriate things are forced on the individual. To protest against these circumstances in the realm of architecture was the purpose of the ink demonstration: my undressing served to protest against the oppression through clothing. Now the naked individual in the natural state was to be established as the herald of protest and placed alongside corrected architecture. &ldquo; (from the protocol, Vienna, January 26, 1968; translation: courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne, 1997)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The action was pushed up to a scandal by the yellow press, mainly because it was seen as an affront against the female alderman for culture, Dr. Sander, &nbsp;who was present at the opening. &nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser held his first speech in the nude on 12 December 1967 at the Hartmann Gallery in Munich, during an action of the &lt;em&gt;Pintorarium&lt;/em&gt; and in presence of the other Pintorarium members, the painters Arnulf Rainer and Ernst Fuchs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The wording of the Munich speech was preserved, whereas the second speech in the nude held shortly after at the International Student Dormitory in Vienna was not recorded. However it exists a protocol from 26 January 1968 in which Hundertwasser exposed the circumstances and motifs for his nude demonstration against rationalism in architecture.&nbsp; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser was invited in connection with the exhibition of his works at the International Student Dormitory to be present at the opening and to speak to the students.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;As he assumed that the building was a modern functional construction, he took along two hollow eggs filled with India ink. He wanted to make a drastic and symbolic change in the architecture by applying black and red ink to the lifeless walls. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser played a record by the painter Arik Bauer (&ldquo;Don&rsquo;t Believe in the T-square&rdquo;), then he threw the two eggs. He quickly undressed and made a speech, stating that the architecture in which the dormitory was built should be rejected and appealing to the students to oppose such oppression which forced them to study in rooms similar to prison cells.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser explained his motifs for the speech in the nude as follows:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&bdquo;It is my conviction that man is surrounded by three layers: by his skin, his clothing and a building. Clothing and buildings have undergone a development in the last centuries which is not longer in tune with nature and the requirements of the individual. As a consequence of the mass aspects of society, inappropriate things are forced on the individual. To protest against these circumstances in the realm of architecture was the purpose of the ink demonstration: my undressing served to protest against the oppression through clothing. Now the naked individual in the natural state was to be established as the herald of protest and placed alongside corrected architecture. &ldquo; (from the protocol, Vienna, January 26, 1968; translation: courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne, 1997)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The action was pushed up to a scandal by the yellow press, mainly because it was seen as an affront against the female alderman for culture, Dr. Sander, &nbsp;who was present at the opening. &nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Die erste &bdquo;Nacktrede&ldquo; hielt Hundertwasser am 12. Dezember 1967 in der Galerie Hartmann in M&uuml;nchen, anl&auml;&szlig;lich einer Aktion des Pintorariums, bei der auch die anderen Mitglieder des Pintorariums, die Maler Arnulf Rainer und Ernst Fuchs, anwesend waren. Der Wortlaut der Rede in M&uuml;nchen ist erhalten, die kurz darauf gehaltene zweite Nacktrede im Internationalen Studentenheim in Wien wurde nicht aufgezeichnet. Jedoch existiert eine Niederschrift vom 26. 1. 1968, in der Hundertwasser die Umst&auml;nde und Motive dieser &bdquo;Nackdemonstration gegen den Rationalismus in der Architektur&ldquo; darlegt.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser war eingeladen worden, anl&auml;&szlig;lich der Er&ouml;ffnung einer Ausstellung seiner Werke im Internationalen Studentenheim zu den Studenten zu sprechen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In der Annahme, da&szlig; es sich beim Bau des Studentenheimes um eine moderne Zweckkonstruktion handle, hatte er zwei mit Tusche angef&uuml;llte hohle Eier zur Er&ouml;ffnung mitgenommen. Er wollte drastisch und sinnf&auml;llig eine Ver&auml;nderung der Architektur durch Applikation von schwarzer und roter Farbe auf die leblosen W&auml;nde vornehmen. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Nach Abspielen einer Schallplatte des Malers Arik Brauer (Glaubt nicht an das Winkelma&szlig;) warf er die beiden Eier. Er entkleidete sich und hielt im nackten Zustand eine Rede dar&uuml;ber, da&szlig; die Architektur, in der das Haus erbaut sei, abzulehnen sei und forderte die Studenten auf, sich gegen den Zwang, in solchen gef&auml;ngnis&auml;hnlichen R&auml;umen zu studieren, zu wehren. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Die Motive f&uuml;r seinen Nacktauftritt erkl&auml;rte Hundertwasser wie folgt:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&bdquo;Meiner &Uuml;berzeugung nach ist der Mensch von drei Schichten umgeben: Von der Haut, von der Kleidung und vom Geb&auml;ude. Kleidung und Geb&auml;ude haben eine Entwicklung genommen, die nicht mehr der Natur und den Bed&uuml;rfnissen des Einzelmenschen entsprechen. Im Zuge der Vermassung der Gesellschaft wird dem Einzelnen das Unangemessene aufgezwungen. Dem Protest gegen diese Umst&auml;nde auf dem Gebiet der Architektur diente die Farbdemonstration, dem Protest gegen die Vergewaltigung durch die Kleidung diente die Entkleidung. So sollte jetzt das nackte, naturbelassene Individuum als Verk&uuml;nder des Protestes statuiert und der korrigierten Architektur an die Seite gestellt werden.&ldquo; (aus der Niederschrift vom 26. 1. 1968)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Die Aktion wurde von der Boulevardpresse zum Skandal erhoben, unter anderem weil man darin eine besondere Br&uuml;skierung der bei der Veranstaltung anwesenden Kulturstadtr&auml;tin Gertrude Sandner sah.&lt;/span&gt;',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'',
text_published_ge-'',
text_author-'Hundertwasser Archiv',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'',
text_source_ge-'',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.3.3.3
object(text,'1.3.3.3','YOUR WINDOW RIGHT, YOUR TREE DUTY',[
id-117,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-117,
txt-'1.3.3.3',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'YOUR WINDOW RIGHT, YOUR TREE DUTY',
text_title_ge-'',
text_keywords-'',
text_date-'1972-02-27',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;We suffocate in our cities because the air is polluted and there is not enough oxygen. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The vegetation which gives us breath and life - we kill it. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Our life becomes unworthy of human beings. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;We pass along grey, sterile facades of buildings, and we do not realise that our houses are prison cells. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;To survive, each of us has to act. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;You must yourself become the author of your environment. You can not wait for a permit or an authority. Not only your clothes and your rooms, but the face of the building in which you live belong to you. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Any kind of individual creation is better than this sterile death. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;You have the right to transform your window and the outside wall around it as far as your arms can reach until your house fits you. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Regulations which are contrary to this right to windows or that forbid or restrict it, should be ignored. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Housing is a human right. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;It is your duty to give all the help you can to the growing vegetation. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The horizontal belongs to nature - the vertical may belong to men. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;All that is white in winter must be green in summer. All that gets wet with rain, all horizontal surfaces under the sky, belong to the realm of plant life. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Woods shall grow on streets and roofs. One must again be able to breathe woodland air in the cities. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The relationship between men and trees must gain a religious dimension. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Then one will understand that it is true if we say: The straight line is godless and immoral.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;We suffocate in our cities because the air is polluted and there is not enough oxygen. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The vegetation which gives us breath and life - we kill it. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Our life becomes unworthy of human beings. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;We pass along grey, sterile facades of buildings, and we do not realise that our houses are prison cells. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;To survive, each of us has to act. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;You must yourself become the author of your environment. You can not wait for a permit or an authority. Not only your clothes and your rooms, but the face of the building in which you live belong to you. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Any kind of individual creation is better than this sterile death. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;You have the right to transform your window and the outside wall around it as far as your arms can reach until your house fits you. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Regulations which are contrary to this right to windows or that forbid or restrict it, should be ignored. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Housing is a human right. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;It is your duty to give all the help you can to the growing vegetation. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The horizontal belongs to nature - the vertical may belong to men. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;All that is white in winter must be green in summer. All that gets wet with rain, all horizontal surfaces under the sky, belong to the realm of plant life. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Woods shall grow on streets and roofs. One must again be able to breathe woodland air in the cities. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The relationship between men and trees must gain a religious dimension. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Then one will understand that it is true if we say: The straight line is godless and immoral.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Wir ersticken in unseren St&auml;dten an Luftverpestung und Sauerstoffmangel. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Die Vegetation, die uns leben und atmen l&auml;&szlig;t, wird systematisch vernichtet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Unser Dasein ist menschenunw&uuml;rdig. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Wir laufen an grauen, sterilen Hausfassaden entlang und sind uns nicht bewu&szlig;t, da&szlig; wir in Gef&auml;ngniszellen eingewiesen sind. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Wenn wir &uuml;berleben wollen, mu&szlig; jeder einzelne handeln. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Du mu&szlig;t selbst deine Umwelt gestalten. Du kannst nicht auf die Obrigkeit und auf Erlaubnis warten. Nicht nur deine Kleidung und dein Innenraum, auch deine Au&szlig;enmauer geh&ouml;rt dir. Jede Art der individuellen Gestaltung ist besser als der sterile Tod.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Es ist dein Recht, dein Fenster und, so weit dein Arm reicht, auch die Au&szlig;enseite so zu gestalten, wie es dir entspricht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Anordnungen, die dieses Fensterrecht verbieten oder einschr&auml;nken, sind zu mi&szlig;achten. Es ist deine Pflicht, der Vegetation mit allen Mitteln zu ihrem Recht zu verhelfen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Freie Natur mu&szlig; &uuml;berall dort wachsen, wo Schnee und Regen hinfallen, wo im Winter alles wei&szlig; ist, mu&szlig; im Sommer alles gr&uuml;n sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Was waagrecht unter freiem Himmel ist, geh&ouml;rt der Natur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Stra&szlig;en und D&auml;cher sollen bewaldet werden. In der Stadt mu&szlig; man wieder Waldluft atmen k&ouml;nnen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Das Verh&auml;ltnis Mensch-Baum mu&szlig; religi&ouml;se Ausma&szlig;e annehmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Dann wird man auch endlich den Satz verstehen: Die gerade Linie ist gottlos.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_occasion_en-'Manifesto for the Eurovision TV show &ldquo;W&uuml;nsch Dir was&ldquo; (Make a Wish) with Dietmar Sch&ouml;nherr and Vivi Bach on 27 February 1972 in Dusseldorf.',
text_occasion_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Manifest f&uuml;r die Eurovision TV-Sendung &bdquo;W&uuml;nsch Dir was&ldquo; mit Dietmar Sch&ouml;nherr und Vivi Bach am 27. Februar 1972 in D&uuml;sseldorf.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Umwelt. Eine kritische Stellungnahme. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;(Environment. A critical comment.) Friedensreich Hundertwasser &ndash; HA Schult. edited by JUNIOR Galerie: Goslar/Germany (Italian, German)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Exhibition catalogue for Haus der Kunst, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Munich&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt; 1975. Gruener Janura AG: Glarus/Switzerland, 1975, pp. 366-367&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreicher, die der Welt geh&ouml;ren. (Austrians who belong to the world) edited by Mobil Oil Austria AG, Vienna. Br&uuml;der Rosenbaum Verlag: Vienna, 1979, p. 94 (German, Text version of 1979)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Catalogues of the World Travelling Museum Exhibition 1975&ndash;1987: &lt;u&gt;French edition:&lt;/u&gt; Paris, Luxembourg, Marseille, Cairo, 1975; Copenhagen, Dakar, 1976; Montreal, Brussels, 1978. &lt;u&gt;English edition:&lt;/u&gt; Tel Aviv, Reykjavik, 1976; Cape Town, Pretoria, Rio de Janeiro, S&atilde;o Paulo, Brasilia, Caracas, 1977; Mexico City, Toronto, 1978; Rome, H&oslash;vikodden, 1980; Helsinki, 1981; London, 1983. &lt;u&gt;German edition:&lt;/u&gt; Warsaw, 1976; Pf&auml;ffikon/Lake Zurich, 1979; Cologne, 1980; Vienna, Graz, 1981. &lt;u&gt;Japanese / English edition: &lt;/u&gt;Tokyo, 1977.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Deutscher Taschenbuch Verlag (dtv): Munich, 1983, pp. 180-181 and ed. 2004 (Langen M&uuml;ller Verlag, Munich), pp. 232-233 (German)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus (The Hundertwasser House). &Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag/Compress Verlag: Vienna, 1985, pp. 100-103 (&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;German&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Rand, Harry: Friedensreich Hundertwasser. Taschen: Cologne, 1991, p. 168, abridged edition 1993 and edition 2003, p. 146&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Umwelt. Eine kritische Stellungnahme. Friedensreich Hundertwasser &ndash; HA Schult. hrg. von JUNIOR Galerie: Goslar/Deutschland (italienisch, deutsch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Katalog zur Ausstellung im Haus der Kunst, M&uuml;nchen 1975. Gruener Janura AG: Glarus/Schweiz 1975, S. 366-367&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreicher, die der Welt geh&ouml;ren. hrsg. von Mobil Oil Austria AG, Wien. Br&uuml;der Rosenbaum Verlag: Wien 1979, S. 94&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Kataloge zur Welt-Wanderausstellung 1975&ndash;1987: &lt;u&gt;Franz&ouml;sische Ausgabe:&lt;/u&gt; Paris, Luxemburg, Marseille, Kairo, 1975; Kopenhagen, Dakar, 1976; Montreal, Br&uuml;ssel, 1978. &lt;u&gt;Englische Ausgabe:&lt;/u&gt; Tel Aviv, Reykjavik, 1976; Cape Town, Pretoria, Rio de Janeiro, S&atilde;o Paulo, Brasilia, Caracas, 1977; Mexiko City, Toronto, 1978; Rom, H&oslash;vikodden, 1980; Helsinki, 1981; London, 1983. &lt;u&gt;Deutsche Ausgabe:&lt;/u&gt; Warschau, 1976; Pf&auml;ffikon (Schweiz), 1979; K&ouml;ln, 1980; Wien, Graz, 1981.&lt;u&gt; Japanische / Englische Ausgabe: &lt;/u&gt;Tokyo, 1977.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Deutscher Taschenbuch Verlag (dtv): M&uuml;nchen 1983, S. 180-181 und Ausgabe 2004 (Langen M&uuml;ller Verlag, M&uuml;nchen), S. 232-233&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; color: red; letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus. &Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag/Compress Verlag: Wien 1985, S. 100-103 &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Rand, Harry: Friedensreich Hundertwasser. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 1991, S. 168, gek&uuml;rzte Ausgabe 1993 und Ausgabe 2003, S. 146&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
