%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.3.3.4.3
object(text,'1.3.3.4.3','LETTER TO THE LANDSCAPE ARCHITECT',[
id-123,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-123,
txt-'1.3.3.4.3',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'LETTER TO THE LANDSCAPE ARCHITECT',
text_title_ge-'',
text_keywords-'',
text_date-'1981-06-12',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Since visiting the tree tenant I have slept poorly. You have helped me like a bear. See Krilow: A hunter had a bear as a true friend. A fly disturbed the hunter`s sleep. Meaning well, the bear took a large rock and killed the fly sitting on the hunter`s nose. Thus was the hunter with all good intentions killed by his true friend, the bear.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The tree tenant should be a provider.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;It should be like a piece of nature from home.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;A piece of spontaneous vegetation in the anonymous, sterile desert of the city. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;A piece of nature which can grow uncontrolled and unregulated by man and his technocracy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The tree tenant, with much foliage and large leaves, should provide humidity and shade, oxygen and beauty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;It must also be very visible from afar as a symbol, visible to many as a regained piece of home.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;However, the oleaster (Eleagnus augustifolia) you have chosen is not a provider.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;It is not a piece from home, because it does not normally occur in the spontaneous vegetation in Vienna`s surroundings. The oleaster has a little foliage, slender leaves, provides little humidity and hardly any shade.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The oleaster as a tree tenant is like a cactus. It limits itself to vegetating and thus pays no or too little rent.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;As a symbol, as a tree seen from afar, the oleaster is unsuited. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Unfortunately, a tree tenant did not move into this building; an intensive-care unit has been built around the wrong plant like one for a seriously ill person in a hospital, with tubes and pipes to feed the tree artificially with water, growth stimulants, fertilizers etc. An automatic switchboard with small flashing green and red lights informing about the tree&rsquo;s progress and needs. Surely a very expensive and proud masterpiece of technology. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The good intention has been completely missed. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Nature has once again been told what to do. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Technocracy has one again won out over nature. Although the opposite was supposed to be demonstrated with the example of the tree tenant: the slow but steady victory of nature over technocracy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;I therefore urgently request:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;to be allowed to change the tree at my expense. I am thinking of indigenous trees &ndash; maple, beech, elder, hornbeam, linden. On the soil just plain grass should grow. Untended. Uncut. Just like in a natural garden: dandelions, plantain, yarrow, nettles, wild oats etc. just like between the walls of old ruins, and not an architect`s plant designed to cover the ground. The mullion and transom must be reinstalled.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The tree tenant should be a tree growing out of a window, not a hole.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The official presentation of the tree tenant can therefore not take place until the crucial changes have been carried out in the manner described above. Time should not be a factor. After all, the tree tenant is supposed to be an example, an easily realised example for the afforestation of cities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;                                                                           &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Since visiting the tree tenant I have slept poorly. You have helped me like a bear. See Krilow: A hunter had a bear as a true friend. A fly disturbed the hunter`s sleep. Meaning well, the bear took a large rock and killed the fly sitting on the hunter`s nose. Thus was the hunter with all good intentions killed by his true friend, the bear.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The tree tenant should be a provider.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;It should be like a piece of nature from home.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;A piece of spontaneous vegetation in the anonymous, sterile desert of the city. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;A piece of nature which can grow uncontrolled and unregulated by man and his technocracy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The tree tenant, with much foliage and large leaves, should provide humidity and shade, oxygen and beauty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;It must also be very visible from afar as a symbol, visible to many as a regained piece of home.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;However, the oleaster (Eleagnus augustifolia) you have chosen is not a provider.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;It is not a piece from home, because it does not normally occur in the spontaneous vegetation in Vienna`s surroundings. The oleaster has a little foliage, slender leaves, provides little humidity and hardly any shade.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The oleaster as a tree tenant is like a cactus. It limits itself to vegetating and thus pays no or too little rent.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;As a symbol, as a tree seen from afar, the oleaster is unsuited. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Unfortunately, a tree tenant did not move into this building; an intensive-care unit has been built around the wrong plant like one for a seriously ill person in a hospital, with tubes and pipes to feed the tree artificially with water, growth stimulants, fertilizers etc. An automatic switchboard with small flashing green and red lights informing about the tree&rsquo;s progress and needs. Surely a very expensive and proud masterpiece of technology. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The good intention has been completely missed. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Nature has once again been told what to do. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Technocracy has one again won out over nature. Although the opposite was supposed to be demonstrated with the example of the tree tenant: the slow but steady victory of nature over technocracy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;I therefore urgently request:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;to be allowed to change the tree at my expense. I am thinking of indigenous trees &ndash; maple, beech, elder, hornbeam, linden. On the soil just plain grass should grow. Untended. Uncut. Just like in a natural garden: dandelions, plantain, yarrow, nettles, wild oats etc. just like between the walls of old ruins, and not an architect`s plant designed to cover the ground. The mullion and transom must be reinstalled.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The tree tenant should be a tree growing out of a window, not a hole.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The official presentation of the tree tenant can therefore not take place until the crucial changes have been carried out in the manner described above. Time should not be a factor. After all, the tree tenant is supposed to be an example, an easily realised example for the afforestation of cities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;                                                                           &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Betrifft: Baummieter Alserbachstrasse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Seit ich den Baummieter besucht habe, habe ich schlecht geschlafen. Sie haben mir da einen B&auml;rendienst erwiesen:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Nach Krilow: Ein J&auml;ger hatte einen B&auml;ren zum treuen Freund. Eine Fliege st&ouml;rte den J&auml;ger im Schlaf. In guter Absicht nahm der B&auml;r einen gro&szlig;en Stein und erschlug die Fliege, die auf des J&auml;gers Nase sa&szlig;. So wurde der J&auml;ger in guter Absicht von seinem treuen Freund, dem B&auml;ren, get&ouml;tet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Der Baummieter soll ein Geber sein. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Er soll wie ein St&uuml;ck Natur der Heimat sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Ein St&uuml;ck Spontanvegetation in der anonymen, sterilen W&uuml;ste der Stadt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Ein St&uuml;ck Natur, das vom Menschen und seiner Technokratie unkontrolliert und unbevormundet wachsen kann. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Der Baummieter soll mit viel Laub und gro&szlig;en Bl&auml;ttern Feuchtigkeit und Schatten, Sauerstoff und Sch&ouml;nheit spenden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Er muss auch als Symbol&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;sehr sichtbar sein,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;viel sichtbar sein&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;wie ein wiedergewonnenes St&uuml;ck Heimat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Doch leider ist die von Ihnen ausgesuchte &Ouml;lweide eleagnus angustifolia kein Geber. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Sie ist kein St&uuml;ck der Heimat, weil sie normalerweise in der Spontanvegetation im Raum um Wien nicht vorkommt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Die &Ouml;lweide hat wenig Laub, schmale Bl&auml;tter, gibt wenig Feuchtigkeit, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;spendet kaum Schatten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Die &Ouml;lweide als Baummieter ist wie ein Kaktus.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Sie beschr&auml;nkt sich darauf zu vegetieren&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Und zahlt daher keine oder zu wenig Miete.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Auch als Symbol, als weithin sichtbarer Baum ist die &Ouml;lweide ungeeignet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Leider ist kein Baummieter eingezogen in dieses Haus, sondern es wurde eine Intensivstation um ein falsches Gew&auml;chs gebaut. Wie f&uuml;r einen Schwerkranken in einer Spezialklinik wird der Baummieter mit angeschlossenen Rohren und Schl&auml;uchen mit Wasser, N&auml;hrfl&uuml;ssigkeit und fl&uuml;ssigen Chemikalien k&uuml;nstlich ern&auml;hrt. Ein automatisches Schaltbrett mit Blinklichtern in Rot und Gr&uuml;n samt Alarmanlage dosiert die Versorgung und wacht &uuml;ber das Befinden des Baumes. Ein s&uuml;ndhaft teures Meisterwerk der Technologie. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Die gute Absicht wurde ins Gegenteil verkehrt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Die Natur ist wieder einmal bevormundet worden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Die Technokratie siegte wieder einmal &uuml;ber die Natur. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Obwohl am Beispiel Baummieter genau das Gegenteil zu demonstrieren w&auml;re: Der langsame, aber stetige Sieg der Natur &uuml;ber die Technokratie. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Ich bitte daher dringend: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;den Baum auf eigene Kosten auswechseln zu d&uuml;rfen. Ich denke an heimische B&auml;ume, Ahorn, Buche, Holunder, Hainbuche, Linde.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Auf dem Erdreich soll einfaches Gras wachsen. Ungepflegt. Ungeschnitten. So wie in einem Naturgarten: L&ouml;wenzahn, Wegerich, Schafgarbe, Brennessel, wilder Hafer usw. so wie zwischen den Mauern alter Ruinen, und nicht eine bodenbedeckerische Architektenpflanze.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Das Fensterkreuz muss wieder installiert werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Der Baummieter soll ein Baum sein, der aus dem Fenster w&auml;chst, statt aus einem Loch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Die offizielle Vorstellung des Baummieters kann daher erst stattfinden, nachdem die entscheidenden &Auml;nderungen im oben beschriebenen Sinne durchgef&uuml;hrt worden sind. Zeit soll kein Faktor sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Der Baummieter soll doch ein Beispiel sein, ein leicht realisierbares Beispiel der Bewaldung der St&auml;dte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_occasion_en-'&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Written in Vienna on 12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;June 1981.&lt;/span&gt;',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser Architecture, For a more human architecture in harmony with nature, Cologne: Benedikt Taschen Verlag, 1997, p. 84&lt;/span&gt;',
text_published_ge-'&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser Architektur, F&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma&quot;&gt;&uuml;r ein natur- und menschengerechteres Bauen, K&ouml;ln: Benedikt Taschen Verlag, 1996, S. 84&lt;/span&gt;',
text_author-'Hundertwasser',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'',
text_source_ge-'',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.3.3.4.4
object(text,'1.3.3.4.4','Tree-tenant initiative, Munich, 1983 MORE',[
id-222,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-222,
txt-'1.3.3.4.4',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'Tree-tenant initiative, Munich, 1983 MORE',
text_title_ge-'',
text_keywords-'',
text_date-'2006-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;On the occasion of the IV. Internationale Gartenbauaustellung IGA (International Garden Show), 1983 Hundertwasser created a poster design and presented his ideas for a more human architecture in harmony with nature by means of the model &ldquo;HIGH-RISE MEADOW HOUSE&rdquo; on a scale of 1:20, which was installed in the Westpark. Moreover he wrote the text &ldquo;Konkrete Utopien f&uuml;r die gr&uuml;ne Stadt&rdquo; (Concrete Utopias for the Green City). &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In addition he planted a tree-tenant on Ganghoferstrasse 86 on July, 26,  1983. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_contents_en-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;On the occasion of the IV. Internationale Gartenbauaustellung IGA (International Garden Show), 1983 Hundertwasser created a poster design and presented his ideas for a more human architecture in harmony with nature by means of the model &ldquo;HIGH-RISE MEADOW HOUSE&rdquo; on a scale of 1:20, which was installed in the Westpark. Moreover he wrote the text &ldquo;Konkrete Utopien f&uuml;r die gr&uuml;ne Stadt&rdquo; (Concrete Utopias for the Green City). &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In addition he planted a tree-tenant on Ganghoferstrasse 86 on July, 26,  1983. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_contents_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Anl&auml;&szlig;lich der IV. Internationalen Gartenbauausstellung 1983 gestaltete Hundertwaser einen Plakatentwurf und pr&auml;sentierte seine Vorstellung einer natur- und menschengerechteren Architektur an Hand des Modelles &bdquo;Hoch-Wiesen-Haus&ldquo; im Ma&szlig;stab 1:20, das im Westpark errichtet wurde. Au&szlig;erdem verfa&szlig;te er den Text &ldquo;Konkrete Utopien f&uuml;r die gr&uuml;ne Stadt&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Zus&auml;tzlich f&uuml;hrte er am 26. Juli 1983 in der Ganghoferstra&szlig;e 86 die Pflanzung eines Baummieters durch. &lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'',
text_published_ge-'',
text_author-'Hundertwasser Archiv',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'',
text_source_ge-'',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.3.4
object(text,'1.3.4','Architecture doctor',[
id-258,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-258,
txt-'1.3.4',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'Architecture doctor',
text_title_ge-'',
text_keywords-'Architecture doctor',
text_date-'0000-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Architecture Doctor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;Our houses have been sick for as long as there have been indoctrinated urban planners and standardised architects. They do not fall sick, but are conceived and brought into the world as sick houses.&lt;br /&gt;These many houses, which we all endure in their thousands, are unfeeling and emotionless, dictatorial, heartless, aggressive, Godless, smooth, sterile, unadorned, gold and unromantic, anonymous and yawningly&nbsp;void.&lt;br /&gt;They are an illusion of functionality. Such is their depressing nature that both their residents and passers-by fall sick. Consider this: while 100 people live in a house, 10,000 walk and drive past it every day; these latter suffer just as much as the residents, if indeed not more so, from the depressing impact of the fa&ccedil;ade of a heartless house. But the hospitals are themselves sick.&lt;br /&gt;Levelling, concentration-camp and barrack-style buildings destroy and standardise the most valuable thing a young person brings to society: spontaneous, individual creativity.&lt;br /&gt;Had architects been able to cure these sick and sick-making buildings, they would not have built them at all.&lt;br /&gt;So a new profession is needed: the architecture doctor.&lt;br /&gt;The sole task of the architecture doctor is to restore human dignity and harmony with nature and human creation. Without first tearing everything down, but by making changes only at strategic points, and without great effort or financial resources. This includes deregulating corrected river courses, breaking up &lt;br /&gt;sterile, flat skylines, converting areas of ground into uneven, undulating surfaces, letting spontaneous vegetation grow in gaps between cobbles and cracks in walls, where it disturbs no one, varying windows and irregularly rounding off corners and edges.&lt;br /&gt;The architecture doctor is also responsible for even more decisive surgical operations, such as cutting away walls and positioning towers and pillars.&lt;br /&gt;We simply need to allow window rights, plant roofs with grass and trees, let climbers grow and install tree tenants.&lt;br /&gt;If you let windows dance by designing them in different styles, and if you allow as many irregularities as possible to appear or happen in fa&ccedil;ades and interiors, houses will recover. Houses will begin to live. Every house, however ugly and sick, can be cured.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Architecture Doctor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;Our houses have been sick for as long as there have been indoctrinated urban planners and standardised architects. They do not fall sick, but are conceived and brought into the world as sick houses.&lt;br /&gt;These many houses, which we all endure in their thousands, are unfeeling and emotionless, dictatorial, heartless, aggressive, Godless, smooth, sterile, unadorned, gold and unromantic, anonymous and yawningly&nbsp;void.&lt;br /&gt;They are an illusion of functionality. Such is their depressing nature that both their residents and passers-by fall sick. Consider this: while 100 people live in a house, 10,000 walk and drive past it every day; these latter suffer just as much as the residents, if indeed not more so, from the depressing impact of the fa&ccedil;ade of a heartless house. But the hospitals are themselves sick.&lt;br /&gt;Levelling, concentration-camp and barrack-style buildings destroy and standardise the most valuable thing a young person brings to society: spontaneous, individual creativity.&lt;br /&gt;Had architects been able to cure these sick and sick-making buildings, they would not have built them at all.&lt;br /&gt;So a new profession is needed: the architecture doctor.&lt;br /&gt;The sole task of the architecture doctor is to restore human dignity and harmony with nature and human creation. Without first tearing everything down, but by making changes only at strategic points, and without great effort or financial resources. This includes deregulating corrected river courses, breaking up &lt;br /&gt;sterile, flat skylines, converting areas of ground into uneven, undulating surfaces, letting spontaneous vegetation grow in gaps between cobbles and cracks in walls, where it disturbs no one, varying windows and irregularly rounding off corners and edges.&lt;br /&gt;The architecture doctor is also responsible for even more decisive surgical operations, such as cutting away walls and positioning towers and pillars.&lt;br /&gt;We simply need to allow window rights, plant roofs with grass and trees, let climbers grow and install tree tenants.&lt;br /&gt;If you let windows dance by designing them in different styles, and if you allow as many irregularities as possible to appear or happen in fa&ccedil;ades and interiors, houses will recover. Houses will begin to live. Every house, however ugly and sick, can be cured.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'',
text_occasion_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Written 24 January, 1990, for publication&nbsp;in the newspaper AZ (Arbeiter Zeitung), Vienna&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'&lt;em&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Newspaper AZ (Arbeiter Zeitung),&nbsp;Vienna, 12 February, 1990&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;',
text_published_ge-'',
text_author-'Hundertwasser',
text_orig_lang-'German',
text_translator-'courtesy Taschen',
text_source_en-'',
text_source_ge-'',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.4.0
object(text,'1.4.0','The Fourth Skin: THE SOCIAL ENVIRONMENT AND IDENTITY',[
id-133,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-133,
txt-'1.4.0',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'The Fourth Skin: THE SOCIAL ENVIRONMENT AND IDENTITY',
text_title_ge-'',
text_keywords-'',
text_date-'2001-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser became only belatedly conscious of his fourth, family skin. An only child, whose father died when he was an infant, his family life was limited to an exclusive relationship with his mother, in the form of a visceral attachment and deep ironic tenderness. When she died in 1972 Hundertwasser came to a decisive turning-point in his career. He became from then on much more sensitive to the social environment and to the identity problems linked to a group, community or nation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fourth skin does not stop at this family level, natural or acquired. Its social milieu extends to the associative groups managing the life of a collectivity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And this Austrian painter feels like a citizen of the world of which he has shaped a new image, that of a happy space in beauty. Beauty engenders peace: peace in the beauty is the sovereign expression of the great natural order, universal harmony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;His brillant power resides in the homogeneity and coherence of his all-embracing vision. Hundertwasser`s geopolitics rest on national identity, on the compactness of the diverse signs that convey the specific difference of a nation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;',
text_contents_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser became only belatedly conscious of his fourth, family skin. An only child, whose father died when he was an infant, his family life was limited to an exclusive relationship with his mother, in the form of a visceral attachment and deep ironic tenderness. When she died in 1972 Hundertwasser came to a decisive turning-point in his career. He became from then on much more sensitive to the social environment and to the identity problems linked to a group, community or nation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fourth skin does not stop at this family level, natural or acquired. Its social milieu extends to the associative groups managing the life of a collectivity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And this Austrian painter feels like a citizen of the world of which he has shaped a new image, that of a happy space in beauty. Beauty engenders peace: peace in the beauty is the sovereign expression of the great natural order, universal harmony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;His brillant power resides in the homogeneity and coherence of his all-embracing vision. Hundertwasser`s geopolitics rest on national identity, on the compactness of the diverse signs that convey the specific difference of a nation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'Hundertwasser ist erst sp&auml;t zu einem Bewu&szlig;tsein der vierten, famili&auml;ren Haut gelangt. Als Einzelkind, das fr&uuml;h den Vater verlor, war sein Familienleben auf die Beziehung zu seiner Mutter beschr&auml;nkt, eine mit einer tiefen ironischen Z&auml;rtlichkeit durchsetzte instinktive Verbundenheit. &hellip;Als sie 1972 stirbt, erreicht Hundertwasser einen entscheidenden Wendepunkt in seiner Karriere, und nun wird er f&uuml;r das soziale Umfeld und die Identit&auml;tsprobleme viel aufgeschlossener, die mit der Zugeh&ouml;rigkeit zu einer Gruppe, einer Gemeinschaft, einer Nation einhergehen. &hellip; F&uuml;r Hundertwasser bleibt die vierte Haut nicht auf die Ebene der Familie beschr&auml;nkt, sei diese die nat&uuml;rlich oder eine erworbene. Das soziale Umfeld erstreckt sich auf die Gesamtheit der Kontakte, die das Leben eines Kollektivs ausmachen. &hellip; Und dieser &ouml;sterreichische Maler f&uuml;hlt sich als B&uuml;rger einer Welt, von der er ein neues Bild schafft, das Bild eines in Sch&ouml;nheit gl&uuml;cklichen Raumes. Aus der Sch&ouml;nheit entsteht der Friede: Der Friede in Sch&ouml;nheit ist der souver&auml;ne Ausdruck der gro&szlig;en nat&uuml;rlichen Ordnung, der universellen Harmonie. &hellip; Die geniale Kraft Hundertwassers liegt in der Homogenit&auml;t und Geschlossenheit seiner globalen Sicht. Hundertwassers Geopolitik beruht auf nationaler Identit&auml;t, auf der Gesamtheit der verschiedenen Zeichen, die die spezifische Eigent&uuml;mlichkeit einer Nation kenntlich machen. ',
text_occasion_en-'',
text_occasion_ge-'',
text_published_en-'',
text_published_ge-'',
text_author-'Pierre Restany',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Pierre Restany, Hundertwasser &ndash; The Painter-King with the Five Skins. TASCHEN, Cologne, 2001, p. 63 ff&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;',
text_source_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Pierre Restany, Die Macht der Kunst, Hundertwasser - Der Maler-K&ouml;nig mit den 5 H&auml;uten, Benedikt Taschen Verlag, K&ouml;ln 1998, S. 63 ff&lt;/p&gt;  ',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

%Andrea###2009-06-26 07:25:11###object###text###1.4.0.1
object(text,'1.4.0.1','I LOVE SCHIELE',[
id-85,
typeOfObject-'TEXT',
text_id-85,
txt-'1.4.0.1',
text_type-'',
text_category-'',
text_title_en-'I LOVE SCHIELE',
text_title_ge-'ICH LIEBE SCHIELE',
text_keywords-'Schiele, Picasso, Klee, Giotto, children, Kinder, Linien, lines, Malerei, painting',
text_date-'1951-00-00',
text_summary_en-'',
text_summary_ge-'',
text_language-'en',
text_contents-'',
text_contents_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I love Schiele, Picasso and Klee and their ilk, and Giotto, the old masters and the like. But in-between and besides them there is a yawning emptiness. The simple is still broad. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I often dream like Schiele, my father, about flowers that are red, and birds and flying fish and gardens in velvet and emerald green and human beings who walk, weeping, in red-yellow and ocean-blue.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Yet I am barred from paradise. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Why does one not let children draw their figures on sidewalks, and their lines on walls and murals in the streets?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I swear, let them draw their lines of pure thick gold.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;En voila une methode de devenir riche par les traits des enfants.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;[Voila, a possibility to get rich through the line drawings of children.]&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Nothing can save you, not Christianity, not Communism, not a bourgeois life; let the children speak, and the painters and architects; let them speak, they who know about a new religion, let those act whom you ridicule, whom you do not notice and who wish you well.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;We are alone.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;We must support people. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;We must build houses. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Nobody supports us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;European man begins to die immediately after he is born, and he is already dead when he is approximately ten years old.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I want to wait until my pain transforms into eternity. Turbulent week. How long? Will I have the strength to wait? I will be alone, today, tomorrow, the day after tomorrow, too?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Je suis pass&eacute; &agrave; 1&#039;autre c&ocirc;t&eacute; de la Seine de Trocadero jusqu&#039;&agrave; la Ponte des Arts. A 1&#039;autre c&ocirc;t&eacute; les T&ecirc;tes etaient petites. &lt;/em&gt;[I crossed to the other side of the Seine, from Trocadero to the Ponte des Arts. On the other side the heads were small.]&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What sounds mean in German sounds beautiful in French: de loin on ne pouvait plus voir les sexes. Faut il vraiement que je moers? Ce que j&#039;&eacute;cris ne me d&eacute;tende pas. Il existent des millions d&#039;hommes qui ne trouvent plus la piti&eacute;. Comment font-ils? Ils ne se suicident pas tous. &nbsp;from the distance one can no longer recognize the sexes. Do I really have to die? What I write, does not relax me. There are millions of people who no longer find pity. How do they manage? Not all of them commit suicide.]&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no island built for me neither here nor beyond. Whatever I will do will decay.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I love only the lines drawn by children, but sadly. For I am not worthy of them. I am knowing, guilty or equally not guilty, I can&rsquo;t become unknowing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Fez. It is a beautiful city that enchanted me, a mosaic of boxes in gray and mosques with emerald stones, and the soil has many colors.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;My life will be without love, M. told me.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Und yet, I am happy at the moment and I always will be.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I will place the color as opulent as the houses here stand together in gray and green.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And I feel it arising in me; it has not deceived me.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not kill me.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schiele should still be alive. I would tell him wonderful things from my journey.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Perhaps it is better that I cannot tell him things, for now I have to tell and give it to everybody.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not kill me beforehand.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A painting by you is good only when it can say more than the drawings of children, when it is equally beautiful as the appearance of ploughed fields and human beings and girls who come towards you, and almost as beautiful as the leaves of trees and grass, as the flowers.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Faisant les peintures n&eacute;es de la douleur&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Je me comprend moins que les autres me comprennent encore &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Les paysages que je parcours et parcourerai&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Je ne les connais pas d&#039;avance&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Mais je deviens de plus en plus riche&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;[To paint pictures born from pain. I understand myself&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;less than others still do. The landscapes which I perambulate&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;and which I still will perambulate, I do not know them before, &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;but I become richer and richer.]&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;',
text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Ich liebe Schiele, Picasso und Klee und ihresgleichen und Giotto, die Alten und ihresgleichen. Doch dazwischen und sonst ist g&auml;hnende Leere. Das Einfache ist weit noch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Ich tr&auml;ume oft wie Schiele, mein Vater, von Blumen, die rot sind, und V&ouml;geln und fliegenden Fischen und G&auml;rten in Samt und Smaragdgr&uuml;n und Menschen, die weinend in Rotgelb und Meerblau gehen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Doch ich bin ausgeschlossen vom Paradies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Warum man die Kinder nicht malen l&auml;&szlig;t am Trottoir ihre Figuren und an den W&auml;nden und Mauern der Stra&szlig;en ihre Linien zeichnen?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Ich schw&ouml;re, la&szlig;t sie zeichnen ihre Linien echten dicken Goldes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;En voila une methode de devenir riche par les traits des enfants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Nichts kann euch retten, nicht Christentum, nicht Kommunismus, nicht B&uuml;rgerlichkeit; la&szlig;t die Kinder sprechen und die Maler und Architekten, la&szlig;t die reden, die von einer neuen Religion wissen, la&szlig;t die handeln, die ihr verlacht, nicht bemerkt und die euch doch Gutes wollen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Wir sind alleine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Wir m&uuml;ssen Menschen st&uuml;tzen &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Wir m&uuml;ssen H&auml;user bauen &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Uns st&uuml;tzt niemand&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Der europ&auml;ische Mensch beginnt sofort, nachdem er geboren ist, zu sterben und ist mit ungef&auml;hr zehn Jahren bereits tot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Ich will warten, bis mein Schmerz sich in Ewigkeit wandelt. Semaine turbulente. Wie lange? Werde ich die Kraft haben zu warten? Alleine werde ich sein heute, morgen, &uuml;bermorgen auch?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Je suis pass&eacute; &agrave; 1&#039;autre c&ocirc;te de la Seine de Trocadero jusqu&#039;&agrave; la Ponte des Arts. A 1&#039;autre c&ocirc;te les Tetes etaient petites.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Sch&ouml;n klingt auf Franz&ouml;sisch, was gemein auf Deutsch: de loin an ne pouvait plus voir les Sexes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Faut il vraiement que je moers? Ce que j&#039;&eacute;cris ne me d&eacute;tende pas. 11 existent des millions d&#039;hommes qui ne trouvent plus la piti&eacute;. Comment fontils? Ils ne se suicident pas tous.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;F&uuml;r mich ist keine Insel gebaut, weder hier noch jenseits. Was ich auch tun werde, wird F&auml;ulnis sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Nur die Linien, von Kindern gezeichnet, liebe ich, doch traurig. Denn ich bin dessen nicht wert. Ich bin wissend, schuldig oder unschuldig-gleich, ich kann nicht unwissend werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;F&egrave;s. Es ist eine sch&ouml;ne Stadt, die mich bezaubert hat, ein Mosaik von Schachteln in Grau und mit Moscheen mit gr&uuml;nen Steinen, und die Erde hat viele Farben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Mein Leben wird ohne Liebe sein, hat mir gesagt M.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Und doch bin ich gl&uuml;cklich momentan und ich werde es immer sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Ich werde die Farbe &lt;/span&gt;so &lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;reich hinsetzen, wie die H&auml;user hier zusammenstehen in Grau und Gr&uuml;n.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Und ich f&uuml;hle es kommen in mir; es hat mich nicht betrogen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Man soll mich nicht t&ouml;ten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Schiele sollte noch leben, ich w&uuml;rde ihm von meiner Reise Wunderbares berichten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Es ist vielleicht besser so, da&szlig; ich ihm nichts sagen kann, denn so mu&szlig; ich es allen sagen und geben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Man soll mich nicht t&ouml;ten vorher.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.4pt&quot;&gt;Eine Malerei von dir ist nur dann gut, wenn sie mehr sagen kann als die Zeichnungen der Kinder, gleich sch&ouml;n ist wie die Formen der gepfl&uuml;gten Felder und wie die Menschen und M&auml;dchen, die &lt;/span&gt;dir entgegengehen und fast so sch&ouml;n wie die Bl&auml;tter der B&auml;ume und Gr&auml;ser, wie die Blumen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Faisant les peintures n&eacute;es de la douleur&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoEnvelopeReturn&quot; style=&quot;margin: 5pt 0cm&quot;&gt;Je me comprend moins que les autres me comprennent encore &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoEnvelopeReturn&quot; style=&quot;margin: 5pt 0cm&quot;&gt;Les paysages que je parcours et parcourerai&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Je ne les connais pas d&#039;avance&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Mais je deviens de plus en plus riche&lt;/p&gt;',
text_occasion_en-'From the diaries 1950/1951.',
text_occasion_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Aus den Tageb&uuml;chern 1950/1951.&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Deutscher Taschenbuch Verlag (dtv): Munich, 1983, pp. 58-59 and ed. 2004 (Langen M&uuml;ller Verlag, Munich), pp. 47-49 (German)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Exhibition catalogue: Hundertwasser &ndash; Kunst &ndash; Mensch &ndash; Natur (Hundertwasser &ndash; Art &ndash; Man &ndash; Nature), Minoritenkloster, Tulln/Austria, 2004, pp. 25-26 (German)&lt;/p&gt;',
text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Deutscher Taschenbuch Verlag (dtv): M&uuml;nchen 1983, S. 58-59 und Ausgabe 2004 (Langen M&uuml;ller Verlag, M&uuml;nchen), S. 47-49 &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Katalog zur Ausstellung Hundertwasser &ndash; Kunst &ndash; Mensch &ndash; Natur. Minoritenkloster, Tulln 2004, S. 25-26&lt;/p&gt;',
text_author-'Hundertwasser',
text_orig_lang-'',
text_translator-'',
text_source_en-'',
text_source_ge-'',
text_excerpt-'',
text_origin-''
]).

